{"id": "13973", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13973", "title": "Verdistis", "text": "Verdistis is a wealthy city, to the northeast of &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nA walled city in the northeasternmost part of the &lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; lands, Verdistis is the home of the richest merchants in the lands, and as such, also the home of the &lt;a href=\"Merchants%20Guild\"&gt;Merchants Guild&lt;/a&gt;, which, alongside financial management, also control permits for those who wish to reside within the city walls. Although technically under Duke Ferol's rule, but with a town council that has developed a reasonable degree of autonomy. Verdistis is well known for its impressive guild houses and the decorous mansions of its noble families. \nThe abundance of wealth has resulted in a proliferation of thieves, seeking to steal their fortune, and assassins, who earn their wage from contracted killing. This in turn has ensured the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves Guild&lt;/a&gt; (operated from the &lt;a href=\"Ducal%20Inn\"&gt;Ducal Inn&lt;/a&gt;) and &lt;a href=\"Assassins%20Guild\"&gt;Assassins Guild&lt;/a&gt; have made their home in this grand city. The merchants themselves work outside the law as much as the guilds themselves, hiring assassins to eliminate those in their way, or paying for the &lt;a href=\"Fireworks\"&gt;destruction of property&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn 1218, a time of orc raids and a plague in &lt;a href=\"Rivertown\"&gt;Rivertown&lt;/a&gt;, Verdistis had issues of its own. Firstly there was a spate of &lt;a href=\"A%20murderer%20in%20Verdistis\"&gt;young women being murdered&lt;/a&gt;. Initially suspected to be the work of &lt;a href=\"Pierce\"&gt;Pierce&lt;/a&gt;, who was seen leaving his &lt;a href=\"Pierce%27s%20Wine%20Barrel\"&gt;residence and business&lt;/a&gt; at night, it was later discovered to be the work of &lt;a href=\"Tutamun\"&gt;Tutamun&lt;/a&gt;, a vampire living in the cellar of the Pierce's residence. Furthermore, the city watch itself was dealing with a political battle: the assassins guild controlled the city from the shadows with most of the watch turning a blind eye to their acts out of cowardice."}
{"id": "18017", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18017", "title": "Verdistis City Watch", "text": "The is a faction in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBackground.\nAs the local guard of &lt;a href=\"Verdistis\"&gt;Verdistis&lt;/a&gt;, the watch is responsible for maintaining law and order. Open cases include &lt;a href=\"A%20Murderer%20in%20Verdistis\"&gt;a string of murders&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Fireworks\"&gt;destruction of property&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough it is run by &lt;a href=\"Commander%20Kratus\"&gt;Commander Kratus&lt;/a&gt;, the watch is primarily under the thumb of the Sirs &lt;a href=\"Dante\"&gt;Dante&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Patrick\"&gt;Patrick&lt;/a&gt;, along with the various guilds, resulting in corruption throughout the ranks of the watch."}
{"id": "18013", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18013", "title": "Verdistis City Watch (building)", "text": " is the home of the &lt;a href=\"Verdistis%20City%20Watch\"&gt;Verdistis City Watch&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Verdistis\"&gt;Verdistis&lt;/a&gt;. It is located to the north of the city entrance.\nBackground.\nResponsible for maintaining law and order in the city, the City Watch's role also extends to investigating crimes committed within it's walls. Led by &lt;a href=\"Commander%20Kratus\"&gt;Commander Kratus&lt;/a&gt; in 1218 AD, the Watch's main focus is on the &lt;a href=\"A%20Murderer%20in%20Verdistis\"&gt;murder of several women&lt;/a&gt; in the night, however, they have very little in the way of leads.\nLayout.\nThe courtyard is cross-shaped and Commander Kratus can be found on the grounds. Opening the main door opens up to the entrance area; there are two tables, with the one on the left having &lt;a href=\"Finnigan\"&gt;Finnigan&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"magic%20lockpicks\"&gt;magic lockpicks&lt;/a&gt; lying on it.\nTo the left of the entrance is &lt;a href=\"Kratus\"&gt;Kratus&lt;/a&gt;' office; if Kratus is not in the courtyard, he can be found here; he will take offence to anyone entering. There is a trap door and a locked door next to the entrance, which can be opened with the platinum key on the table next to the bed inside Kratus' office. South of the office is the locked storage with various pieces of equipment stored within.\nTo the right of the entrance is a dining area where, along with other food, a &lt;a href=\"Roasted%20Pork\"&gt;roasted pork&lt;/a&gt; can be found. South of the dining area, the prison can be found."}
