{"id": "19427", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19427", "title": "Vitality", "text": "Vitality or health as it is known in later games, is the potential damage a &lt;a href=\"characters\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; can take in the \"Divinity\" &lt;a href=\"series\"&gt;series&lt;/a&gt;. For the &lt;a href=\"player%20characters\"&gt;player characters&lt;/a&gt; throughout the series, it is a &lt;a href=\"derived%20statistics\"&gt;derived statistic&lt;/a&gt; that can only be increased permanently via the levelling of &lt;a href=\"attributes\"&gt;attributes&lt;/a&gt; or or temporarily via equipment.\nDivine Divinity.\nVitality cannot be increased during leveling directly, but &lt;a href=\"Constitution%23Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; affects vitality to a varying degree depending on the class. Vitality can also be affected by &lt;a href=\"Charms%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29%23Vitality\"&gt;Charms&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bless%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;Bless&lt;/a&gt; and various Prefixes and Suffixes on gear."}
