{"id": "17003", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17003", "title": "Water Arrow", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in ' and '\nCharacteristics.\n is a special arrow which deals water damage and inflicts &lt;a href=\"Wet%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Wet Status&lt;/a&gt; (2 turns) to all characters in area of impact where the arrow will also create a water surface (2 meter radius). Note that if character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Chilled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Chilled Status&lt;/a&gt; using this arrow will cause the character to be affected by &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen Status&lt;/a&gt;. Likewise if character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked Status&lt;/a&gt; this arrow will cause the character to be affected by &lt;a href=\"Stunned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Stunned Status&lt;/a&gt;. These statuses are applied only if character has no Magic Armour.\nCharacters need to wield &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Weapons\"&gt;bow or crossbow&lt;/a&gt; in order to use this arrow. The damage of the arrow depends on: base damage of the wielded weapon, &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and height (bonus from height difference is affected by &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt;).\nSince is a special arrow it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Arrow Recovery&lt;/a&gt; talent which grants 33 % chance to recover a special arrow after firing it. This arrow is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Elemental Ranger&lt;/a&gt; talent that grants additional elemental damage bonus depending on the surface the shooting character is standing in. It is possible to increase the range of the arrow by 2 meters through the &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for."}
