{"id": "12149", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12149", "title": "Water Essence", "text": "Water essence is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Items\"&gt;crafting component&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"\nDescription.\nA blue orb imbued with the essence of water. On its own it has no use. However, it is a key component in crafting &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; scrolls and &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Nimble%20Tumble\"&gt;Potions of Nimble Tumble&lt;/a&gt;. It can also be used to create &lt;a href=\"Freezing%20Arrow\"&gt;freezing arrows&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe higher the quality the more powerful scroll can be crafted from it. More powerful orbs can be used to craft less powerful scrolls.\nLocation.\nCreatures.\nFollowing table shows all creatures which have a chance to drop the item upon death. Highlighted creatures in this table have 100 % chance to drop said item. Note that creatures may drop other items as well.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for. Note that for more powerful Hydrosophist scrolls a better quality Water essence is required. If the scroll utilises base water essence it is possible to use higher quality essence as substitute. In short you cannot use \"Water Essence\" in recipe requiring \"Alien Water Essence\" or \"High Quality Water Essence\"."}
{"id": "20097", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20097", "title": "Water Infusion", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive mixed skill that allows caster to change their summoned Incarnate's element to water. By changing the element, the Incarnate gains multiple boons associated with it. Its basic close attack will deal water damage. Due to the Incarnate being infused with water it gains Water Resistance + 100 % but it suffer from decreased resistances: Fire Resistance - 20 %. Besides Water resistance being increased the Incarnate becomes immune to &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt; status effect. Alongside this the Incarnate learns the Hydrosophist skill &lt;a href=\"Restoration%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Restoration&lt;/a&gt;. \nNote that the effects of are achieved by summoning the Incarnate unto any water surface.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophy\"&gt;Hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into both &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a any non-source &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks are combined. Since is a mixed skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nLocation.\nTraders.\nThis spell cannot be bought or stolen from any NPCs in the game.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift Bag: Pet Power allows this skill to be used on any summoned creature. This gift bag also shortens the cooldown of this skill from 3 turns to 1 turn. Following table shows what skills will specific summoned entity gain from . Note that there are no changes to the skill and bonuses granted by the skill to the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "10957", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10957", "title": "Water Resistance Potion (Original Sin 2)", "text": "The Water Resistance Potion is a &lt;a href=\"Consumables%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;consumable item&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nWater resistance potion is a consumable potion that grants + 15 % Water resistance for 3 turns. If character has \"&lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt;\", the potion will grant + 30 % Water resistance instead of + 15 %. The potions weight is 0.25 and its value is 30 gold.\nMedium water resistance potion is a consumable potion that grants + 50 % Water resistance for 3 turns. If character has \"Five-Star Diner talent\", the potion will grant + 100 % Water resistance instead of + 50 %. The potions weight is 0.25 and its value is 45 gold.\nLarge water resistance potion is a consumable potion that grants 75 % Water resistance for 2 turns. If character has \"Five-Star Diner talent\", the potion will grant + 150 % Water resistance instead of + 75 %. The potions weight is 0.25 and its value is 150 gold.\nHuge water resistance potion is a consumable potion that grants 90 % Water resistance for 2 turns. If character has \"Five-Star Diner talent\", the potion will grant + 180 % Water resistance instead of + 90 %. The potions weight is 0.25 and its value is 450 gold.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of potions and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs."}
