{"id": "17769", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17769", "title": "Rainwater amulet", "text": ""}
{"id": "12230", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12230", "title": "Raise Bloated Corpse", "text": "Raise bloated corpse is a &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a summoning necromancer skill that allows caster to conjure a Bloated Corpse out of any dead body (be it enemy, neutral or ally) that will fight for the summoner for 10 turns. The corpse will deal physical damage with its basic close range attacks and leave a trail of blood when it moves and perishes. The corpse has + 200 % Poison Resistance that allows it to heal from any poison damage done, but takes increased fire damage as it has - 20 % Fire Resistance. The corpse has no Physical or Magic armour. If the corpse is conjured while the caster has summoned an &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;, the Incarnate will immediately expire as the two cannot be summoned at the same time.\nThe has access only to one skill &lt;a href=\"Vile%20Burst\"&gt;Vile Burst&lt;/a&gt; which will cause it to explode and deal large amount of physical damage. The skill deals damage to all characters caught in its blast which has 3 meter radius. The damage seems to be reflected back, however since the skill causes the Bloated Corpse to die it is obsolete.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Necromancy\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Necromancy%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Necromancy Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a starter Necromancer skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Necromancer skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 60 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves varies. The AP cost to cast the as a skill is 1 AP and the cost to cast as a scroll is 2 AP. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a summoning skill and as such it is primarily affected by Level, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; ability of the caster. Due to the bloated corpse relying heavily on physical attacks and skills it also receives large bonus from Warfare ability. The Bloated Corpse begins to receive points into Warfare when caster is level 3. Following table shows at which level the corpse receives points into Warfare.\n properties can be affected by talents and skills. With the exception of infusions, which do not work in the base game, the bloated corpse can be buffed the same way as any allied character or companion. Note that while &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt; warfare skill will boost its attack it will make it unable to cast Vile Burst as it will be &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt;. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell necromancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only \"&lt;a href=\"Tarquin\"&gt;Tarquin&lt;/a&gt;\" is guaranteed to follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; as they travel with &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;. \"&lt;a href=\"Jahan\"&gt;Jahan&lt;/a&gt;\" may join the Godwoken on the ship as well if his demands are met. \nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift bag: Pet Power allows the player to infuse not only their Incarnate but also all other summoned creatures. This includes \"Bloated Corpse\" as well. Note that skills gained by infusing it, may differ from skills gained by infusing other summoned creatures."}
{"id": "12377", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12377", "title": "Raise Bone Widow", "text": " is an &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;adept Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a summoning necromancer skill that allows caster to conjure a giant &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; bone spider in any visible area in 13 meter radius that will fight for the summoner for 5 turns. The spider will deal physical damage with its basic close range attacks. The spider has + 200 % Poison Resistance that allows it to heal from any poison damage done and has + 20 % to all other elemental Resistances. The spider starts with some Physical armour but no Magic Armour. \nThe spider possesses 2 talents: &lt;a href=\"Opportunist%20%28Talent%29\"&gt;Opportunist&lt;/a&gt; that allows it to attack any enemy that moves past it and &lt;a href=\"Undead%20%28Talent%29\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; which is its racial talent and source of high Poison Resistance. Alongside talents there are 2 skills at its disposal: &lt;a href=\"Burrow\"&gt;Burrow&lt;/a&gt; that allows it to teleport itself to any otherwise unreachable area and &lt;a href=\"Devour%20Corpse\"&gt;Devour Corpse&lt;/a&gt; which allows it to consume intact (unused) corpses for damage boost.\nIf the spider is conjured while the caster has summoned an &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;, the Incarnate will immediately expire as the two cannot be summoned at the same time.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Necromancy\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Necromancy%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Necromancy Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is an adept Necromancer skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 9.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 260 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves varies. The AP cost to cast as a skill is 2 AP whilst the AP cost for casting scroll is 3 AP.\nBoth the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a summoning skill and as such it is primarily affected by Level, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; ability of the caster. Due to the Bone Widow relying heavily on physical attacks and skills it also receives large bonus from Warfare ability. The Bone Widow begins to receive points into Warfare when caster is level 1 and receives additional points into it every 2 levels up to 10 points into Warfare (caster reaches level 19). Following table shows at which level of the caster the spider receives points into Warfare.\n properties can be affected by talents and skills. With the exception of infusions, which do not work in the base game, the Bone Widow can be buffed the same way as any allied character or companion. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell necromancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only \"&lt;a href=\"Tarquin\"&gt;Tarquin&lt;/a&gt;\" is guaranteed to follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; as they travel with &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;. \"&lt;a href=\"Jahan\"&gt;Jahan&lt;/a&gt;\" may join the Godwoken on the ship as well if his demands are met. \nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift bag: Pet Power allows the player to infuse not only their Incarnate but also all other summoned creatures. This includes the \"Bone Widow\" as well. Note that skills gained by infusing it, may differ from skills gained by infusing other summoned creatures."}
