{"id": "3803", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3803", "title": "Ransid", "text": "Ransid is a beggar you encounter on &lt;a href=\"Lanilor%20Lane\"&gt;Lanilor Lane&lt;/a&gt; outside &lt;a href=\"Chez%20Chanelle\"&gt;Chez Chanelle&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nLike &lt;a href=\"Madam%20Eve\"&gt;Madam Eve&lt;/a&gt;, he is upset that the city's Champions won't help him. He offers a quest, and can provide some background information on the city's &lt;a href=\"Playhouse\"&gt;Playhouse&lt;/a&gt;.\nRelated quests.\nRansid asks you to retrieve his mother-in-law's earrings from the Playhouse so he can buy \"some bread\". If you offer to give him bread, he insists on getting the earrings instead.\nOnce you complete this quest in the Playhouse, you gain access to a room in the back where you meet Mara, the &lt;a href=\"Ghost\"&gt;spirit&lt;/a&gt; of Ransid's deceased mother-in-law. You obtain &lt;a href=\"Mara%27s%20Earrings\"&gt;Mara's Earrings&lt;/a&gt; after a short dialog in which you learn that Ransid is a drunk and a gambler."}
