{"id": "2826", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2826", "title": "Raze's Flying Fortress", "text": "Raze's Flying Fortress is a fortress found in &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt;, located on a cliff directly in front of &lt;a href=\"Champion%20Harbour\"&gt;Champion Harbour&lt;/a&gt;. It is controlled &lt;a href=\"Raze\"&gt;General Raze&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt;, and features a lava setting with level 27-29 enemies.\nLayout.\nProceed north towards the headquarters portal. There are platforms at varying elevations along the way, each with plenty of air defences and ground enemies; there are also a few &lt;a href=\"herbs\"&gt;herbs&lt;/a&gt; and seven golden chests, one containing the &lt;a href=\"Hunter%20Ring\"&gt;Hunter Ring&lt;/a&gt;, part of the &lt;a href=\"Hunter%20armour%20set\"&gt;Hunter armour set&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe headquarters is a relatively small area. A &lt;a href=\"Books%20and%20notes%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; titled &lt;a href=\"Old%20Message\"&gt;Old Message&lt;/a&gt; can be found on a table in the first room, written by Raze to &lt;a href=\"Ba%27al\"&gt;Ba'al&lt;/a&gt;, discussing &lt;a href=\"Raze%27s%20Cuirass\"&gt;Raze's Cuirass&lt;/a&gt;. Further ahead, there are three closed doors to the north. Behind the second door is a chest containing the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Armor\"&gt;Crystal Dragon Leggings&lt;/a&gt; and other loot. Behind the third door is a key; take it and proceed south, using the key to unlock the door.\nIn the next room turn east and go up the stairs to find Raze, who complains of being cold despite being surrounded by lava. &lt;a href=\"Mindread\"&gt;Mindread&lt;/a&gt; him to obtain &lt;a href=\"Ulthring%27s%20Leggings\"&gt;Ulthring's Leggings&lt;/a&gt; upon his death, along with &lt;a href=\"Raze%27s%20Cuirass\"&gt;Raze's Cuirass&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Divinity%20II%20quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Raging%20Raze\"&gt;Raging Raze&lt;/a&gt; (if &lt;a href=\"Wesson\"&gt;Wesson&lt;/a&gt; was chosen as &lt;a href=\"The%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;The Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Enchanter\"&gt;Enchanter&lt;/a&gt;). This can be a difficult fight as he uses two healing chambers when his health gets low. There are levers next to the chambers that temporarily disable them, so there is a limited time frame to kill him before he hops into one of those chambers again."}
