{"id": "3649", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3649", "title": "Reflect", "text": "Reflect is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Warrior\"&gt;Warrior skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nReflect is a passive Warrior skill that gives the Knight an ability to reflect certain portion of damage dealt to them back at their source. Due to its nature, once learnt, it will be always active and does not require any specific weapon to be equipped. "}
{"id": "15196", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15196", "title": "Reflect Missiles", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20skills%23Way%20of%20the%20warrior\"&gt;Warrior skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nReflect missiles is a passive skill that reflects ranged attacks aimed at &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; back to the enemies that fired them. The reflected missiles do small amount of original damage upon hit. Since it is a passive skill it is always in effect and does not cost magic. This skill also has a melee version called &lt;a href=\"Repel%20Damage\"&gt;Repel Damage&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3651", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3651", "title": "Regenerate", "text": "Regenerate is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Warrior\"&gt;Warrior skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nRegenerate is a passive Warrior skill that increases the speed with which the Knights life-force is restored in their &lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; form. Due to its nature, once learnt, it will be always active. Note that there is additional skill text for this skill which says, \"This bonus is added to the regenerate rate based on your character's strength and equipment.\"\u00a0 While this skill effects both base stats and gear it still yields small returns after the first level."}
{"id": "20256", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20256", "title": "Regenerating (Status)", "text": "Regenerating is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nRegenerating is a positive skill and environmental status effect. Afflicted characters will gradually restore set amount of Vitality each turn. \nCause.\nRegenerating can be acquired via either surface or spell. On Rivellon it is the \"blessed poison surface\" and \"blessed poison cloud\" which will provide Regenerating status to all characters in its vicinity. \nTreatment.\nRegenerating is a positive status effect, therefore it automatically ignores armour values and resistances. It can only be cancelled through &lt;a href=\"Bleeding%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Bleeding&lt;/a&gt; status effect which can be applied through the following means, but only if character does not have Physical armour or is not &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;:"}
