{"id": "11381", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11381", "title": "Ricochet (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Ricochet is a &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;starter Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nFire a normal arrow that harms multiple foes at once. The first attack will find another target within 5m of the first one. Forks up to two times.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. Since is a starter Huntsman skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Huntsman skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well.\nSince is a weapon based skill and as such it does not have a scroll. It is also not possible to craft a skillbook.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell huntsman skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell."}
