{"id": "2813", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2813", "title": "Risk Life for Limb", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; given by &lt;a href=\"Jonelath\"&gt;Jonelath&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDetailed Walkthrough.\nRisk Life for Limb is a &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; given by &lt;a href=\"Jonelath\"&gt;Jonelath&lt;/a&gt; for the second upgrade to the &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Necromancer's Ring&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Tower\"&gt;Battle Tower&lt;/a&gt;. You must find and defeat &lt;a href=\"Xanlosch\"&gt;Xanlosch&lt;/a&gt; (level 27) and his creature &lt;a href=\"Isabelle\"&gt;Isabelle&lt;/a&gt; and take a limb from her to bring it back to him.\nXanlosch is located in &lt;a href=\"Stone%27s%20Flying%20Fortress\"&gt;Stone's Flying Fortress&lt;/a&gt; near the teleporter that takes you to &lt;a href=\"Stone\"&gt;Stone&lt;/a&gt;. The shield generator near him prevents you from taking &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Form\"&gt;Dragon Form&lt;/a&gt; and if you destroy it before defeating him, he will call out two fighting buddies in the air named &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Wahat\"&gt;Lord Wahat&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Admiral%20Mirihim\"&gt;Admiral Mirihim&lt;/a&gt; who will attack you from the air. Watch out for his arrows as they can be deadly.\nXanlosch drops &lt;a href=\"Ulthring%27s%20Gauntlets\"&gt;Ulthring's Gauntlets&lt;/a&gt; if you perform a &lt;a href=\"mindread\"&gt;mindread&lt;/a&gt; before killing him."}
{"id": "3905", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3905", "title": "Rivellon", "text": "Rivellon is the world within which the Divinity &lt;a href=\"series\"&gt;series&lt;/a&gt; takes place. Although vast in size, Rivellon is the known world, the planet itself has not been fully explored by its residents and there are records of explorers from unknown lands venturing into its boundaries.\nWorld map.\nPresented initially in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\" as 4 key areas, &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt; consuming the majority of the northern section of the map is dominated by &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;s, with the exception of the &lt;a href=\"Verdistis\"&gt;Verdistis&lt;/a&gt;' underground which is largely occupied by the &lt;a href=\"lizard\"&gt;lizard&lt;/a&gt;s, the mountain range &lt;a href=\"Tanoroth\"&gt;Tanoroth&lt;/a&gt; to the west, the native home of the &lt;a href=\"Dwarf\"&gt;dwarves&lt;/a&gt;, who also have a single outpost within Ferol itself. To the south is the dark forest of &lt;a href=\"Teneb%20Tiriel\"&gt;Teneb Tiriel&lt;/a&gt;, home of the &lt;a href=\"Elf\"&gt;elves&lt;/a&gt;, who also maintain an outpost on the Teneb Tirel/Ferol border. In the south east is &lt;a href=\"Yuthul%20Gor\"&gt;Yuthul Gor&lt;/a&gt;, the domain of the &lt;a href=\"orc\"&gt;orc&lt;/a&gt;s, which is the only location not seen in the game itself.\n\"&lt;a href=\"Divinity%20II\"&gt;Divinity II&lt;/a&gt;\" saw the introduction of &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt; to the west of Tanoroth and due south of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Farglow\"&gt;Farglow&lt;/a&gt; is located. Based on its location on the eastern side of Tanoroth and its southern position, Farglow is nestled to the west of Teneb Tirel. In the waters to the south west of the mainland, &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island\"&gt;Sentinel Island&lt;/a&gt; sits.\nWith \"\" taking place 1000 years before \"Divine Divinity\", it is not possible to discern if &lt;a href=\"Cyseal\"&gt;Cyseal&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Glen\"&gt;Silver Glen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Luculla%20Forest\"&gt;Luculla Forest&lt;/a&gt; are truly distinct from the locations we already know of, or if in fact, they have been abandoned and replaced with other civilisations.\nIn \"\" we see the introduction of &lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Eye\"&gt;Reaper's Eye&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Coast\"&gt;Reaper's Coast&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Spine\"&gt;Dragon's Spine&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stormdale\"&gt;Stormdale&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Arx\"&gt;Arx&lt;/a&gt; contained within the southern peninsula of the continent they are a part of.\nThe lands in \"\" retain the same names, but their position, size and shape differs vastly between maps. Even the continents themselves do not retain the same form."}
{"id": "15879", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15879", "title": "Rivellon Fries", "text": "Rivellon Fries is a in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n are a consumable item which will heal 20 % of maximum Vitality and grant + 2 points to &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; upon consuming. If character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; it will heal 40 % of maximum Vitality and grant + 4 points to Constitution. The effect of last 6 turns.\nPoisoned is a consumable item that was poisoned through various means (either &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Bottle%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;poison bottle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Zaikk%27s%20Talon\"&gt;Zaikk's Talon&lt;/a&gt;). Poisoning the will reduce its value to 0. Instead of healing it will deal poison damage equal to 20 % of the consumers maximum Vitality, rendering it unsafe for the living but safe for &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; and grant + 2 points to &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt;. \nIf character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; the will deal poison damage equal to 40 % of the consumers maximum Vitality and grant + 4 points to Constitution. The effects last 6 turns. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of food and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs."}
{"id": "3726", "revid": "3206664", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3726", "title": "Rivellon Guards", "text": ""}
{"id": "3738", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3738", "title": "Rivellon Guards Armour", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special armour&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nRivellon Guards Armour is a special cuirass that is part of the &lt;a href=\"Rivellon%20Guards%20Set\"&gt;Rivellon Guards Set&lt;/a&gt;. The set is constituted of &lt;a href=\"Rivellon%20Guards%20Armour\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rivellon%20Guards%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Rivellon%20Guards%20Warhammer\"&gt;warhammer&lt;/a&gt;. The armour requires atleast level 6 in order to be worn. When worn the armour will boost Magic Armour Rating + 1 point. The armour can also be improved by 1 charm and 1 enchantment. The default enchantment on this armour is Increased Mana which increases Mana by 10 points. \nHow to Obtain.\nIt can be looted from the chest after defeating Lord &lt;a href=\"Arben\"&gt;Arben&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"To%20Lay%20a%20Ghost%20to%20Rest\"&gt;To Lay a Ghost to Rest&lt;/a&gt; quest in the tomb found beneath the &lt;a href=\"Chapel\"&gt;Chapel&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley%20Village\"&gt;Broken Valley Village&lt;/a&gt;.\nSet Properties.\nRivellon Guards Armour is a part of the set Rivellon Guards Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Rivellon Guards Armour primary increased attribute is Melee Armour Rating, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping the final third item from the set."}
{"id": "3739", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3739", "title": "Rivellon Guards Leggings", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special leggings&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nRivellon Guards Leggings are special leggings that are part of the &lt;a href=\"Rivellon%20Guards%20Set\"&gt;Rivellon Guards Set&lt;/a&gt;. The set is constituted of &lt;a href=\"Rivellon%20Guards%20Armour\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rivellon%20Guards%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Rivellon%20Guards%20Warhammer\"&gt;warhammer&lt;/a&gt;. The leggings require atleast level 8 in order to be worn. When worn the leggings will boost Ranged Armour Rating by 2. Furthermore it will boost &lt;a href=\"Vitality\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; attribute by 2 points. The leggings can be improved by 2 enchantments. The default enchantments on these leggings are Magic Damage Aura and Ranged Protection.\nHow to Obtain.\nLeggings can be bought from blacksmith &lt;a href=\"Derk\"&gt;Derk&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley%20Village\"&gt;Broken Valley village&lt;/a&gt;. \nSet Properties.\nRivellon Guards Leggings is a part of the set Rivellon Guards Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Rivellon Guards Leggings primary increased attribute is Ranged Armour Rating, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping the final third item from the set."}
{"id": "3725", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3725", "title": "Rivellon Guards Set", "text": "This armor and weapon set is available only in \"\".\nIt contains the following pieces:\n\"The Rivellon Guards are plentiful in number, being the prime protectors of the many villages that dot the glades and vales, but that does not mean they are not a force to be reckoned with, even individually. For without them mankind would be doomed to fall prey to many, many foes that threaten civilisation. Dragon Slayers and Aleroth Champions may form the fists of the human military body, but the Rivellon Guards, they are the backbone.\nGuard armours have to be versatile as they must serve under many conditions: they must be light enough to be worn all day, but strong enough to withstand blade and arrow; flexible enough to be able to chase brigands up mountain paths and through thick forests, but up to the challenge when their wearer is ambushed by a troll or goblin raiding party. Striking a balance between so many requirements is not easy, but years of tradition have supplied the Rivellon Guards with the best of the best.\""}
{"id": "3851", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3851", "title": "Rivellon Guards Warhammer", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Weapons%23One-Handed%20Warhammer\"&gt;special warhammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nRivellon Guards Warhammer is a special warhammer which is part of &lt;a href=\"Rivellon%20Guards%20Set\"&gt;Rivellon Guards set&lt;/a&gt;. The set is constituted of &lt;a href=\"Rivellon%20Guards%20Armour\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rivellon%20Guards%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Rivellon%20Guards%20Warhammer\"&gt;warhammer&lt;/a&gt;. The warhammer requires atleast level 14 in order to be used. When used it will boost &lt;a href=\"Conditioned%20Body\"&gt;Conditioned Body&lt;/a&gt; by 2 points and &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Chance\"&gt;Critical Chance&lt;/a&gt; by 3 points. The warhammer can be improved by 1 charm and 1 enchantment. The default enchantment on this warhammer is Increased Magical Damage.\nHow to Obtain.\nThe hammer is a reward for completing the quest &lt;a href=\"Lost%20for%20Words\"&gt;Lost for Words&lt;/a&gt;. \nSet Properties.\nRivellon Guards Warhammer is a part of the set Rivellon Guards Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Rivellon Guards Warhammers primary increased attribute is Magic Damage, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping the final third item from the set."}
