{"id": "17928", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17928", "title": "Rivertown Armoury Shop", "text": " is a shop in &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nLocated just north from &lt;a href=\"Doctor%20Elrath%27s%20house\"&gt;Doctor Elrath's house&lt;/a&gt;, as the name suggests, this shop primarily sells &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20Armour\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Gero\"&gt;Gero&lt;/a&gt; handles the merchandise, whereas &lt;a href=\"Mathieu\"&gt;Mathieu&lt;/a&gt; merely works there.\nLayout.\nThe entrance leads to the main shop area. A Counter is standing to the left of the entry. In the shop, there are a couple weapon closets, one armour closet, as well as a few pieces of armour next to the eastern wall.\nThe back room serves as a living area for the merchants. The back door is locked, but can be opened with &lt;a href=\"Lockpick%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;lockpick&lt;/a&gt; (level 3), although it's not necessary to unlock it."}
{"id": "15241", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15241", "title": "Rivertown Market", "text": " is a great trading hub in &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nFocused on bartering, there are many shops and merchants. The middle portion is reserved for food mercants, and there is also hatch down to &lt;a href=\"Rivertown%20Sewers\"&gt;Rivertown Sewers&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe main merchant buildings are placed around the middle part. Going clockwise there is an unoccupied house, the apothecary, Blake's General Store, Ars Magicana, Geoff's Hardware, Rivertown Armoury Shop, and Doctor Elrrath's House.\nLieutenant Robin is stationed between Ars Magicana and Blake's General Store. There is also a vast number of soldiers. Tingalf can be found right next to Geoff's Hardware, and Marcus, along with Moll, is standing right at the southern entrance.\nBehind Ars Magicana an &lt;a href=\"augmentor\"&gt;augmentor&lt;/a&gt; grows, and a teleporter and unfinished pit can be found. Another augmentor can be found due east, next to Romeo's House."}
{"id": "17819", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17819", "title": "Rivertown Sewers", "text": " is a sewer network underneath Rivertown.\nLayout.\nBeing a sewer, the place is dark, with a wide varriety of &lt;a href=\"Lizards%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;Lizards&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;. \nComing from Rivertown Market, to the east is storage area, with a vast number of containers, some of which are locked and trapped. On top of one of the boxes is Bronze key, which opens the leftmost flat-lid chest in the nothern row.\nThis place is also involved in the black market mystery quest chain in Rivertown Market.\nRight to the west of the entrance from Rivertown Market ladder is a big cask of beer.\nWest of there is a skeleton, apparently a torture victim. Most likely the &lt;a href=\"ghost\"&gt;ghost&lt;/a&gt; nearby is a victim too.\nEven more west, before the crossroads, a &lt;a href=\"Restoration%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;Restoration&lt;/a&gt; skillbook can be found in a ravine. It needs &lt;a href=\"Telekinesis%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;Telekinesis&lt;/a&gt; to reach it.\nA &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Skeleton\"&gt;Summon Skeleton&lt;/a&gt; skillbook is also found on top of the barrels.\nSouth from the crossroads is another batch that needs Telekinesis to reach, and further on from this batch is a skillbook for &lt;a href=\"Spellshield\"&gt;Spellshield&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlong the way there are Greater Ghouls, spidermine traps and Lizards.\nNorthwest of the Greater Ghouls is a small room containing a number of potions. \nDue west from the potion room is another treasure room, which is guarded by a variety of Lizards, including &lt;a href=\"Lizards%23Fanatic%20Lizard\"&gt;Fanatic Lizards&lt;/a&gt;.\nAt the most southern reach a small room with treasure can be found, but there is also a vast number of &lt;a href=\"Scorpion\"&gt;Scorpions&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Steel%20Scorpions\"&gt;Steel Scorpions&lt;/a&gt; there as well. Before this room a single Steel Scorpion is encountered.\nNear this Scorpion room is also a small number of jewels.\nOtherwise there are Garbage, Broken Bottles, Rotten Food, Fish and variety of containers like Barrels and Chests around."}
{"id": "17813", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17813", "title": "Rivertown Watch", "text": " is a barracks in &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nLocated just south of &lt;a href=\"Stormfist%20Castle\"&gt;Stormfist Castle&lt;/a&gt;, the Rivertown watch acts as a small barracks as well as a command post for &lt;a href=\"Commmander%20Ralpheus%20Neodrim\"&gt;Commmander Ralpheus Neodrim&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nThe entrance opens to a small hall with a meeting table. Across from the entrance are Ralph's personal quarters. Going to the right from entrance is a small armoury and after this armoury a small dining area can be found. The dining area contains a hatch down to the prison. The prison itself is small, with room for two prisoners. It also holds a couple of chests."}
