ith &lt;a href=\"Precise%20Incision\"&gt;Precise Incision&lt;/a&gt; in Enhanced Edition. Reflecting the ability change the Rogue wields two &lt;a href=\"Fighting%20Knife\"&gt;Fighting knives&lt;/a&gt; instead of one. Another difference is that instead of 1 Minor Healing potion they have 2 Minor Healing potions and additionally the Rogue has &lt;a href=\"Smoke%20Grenade\"&gt;Smoke Grenade&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "10592", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10592", "title": "Rogue (Original Sin 2)", "text": "The rogue is a &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;survivor class&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nSummary.\nRogue is a survivor who uses their &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; skill in combination with their &lt;a href=\"Dual%20Wielding\"&gt;Dual-Wielding&lt;/a&gt; skill. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt;. They primarily wield daggers in both hands. \nTheir first starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Knife\"&gt;Throwing Knife&lt;/a&gt; with which they can damage their foes from distance. The second starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Backlash\"&gt;Backlash&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to teleport behind their foe and deal damage to them and their final starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Adrenaline%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Adrenaline&lt;/a&gt; which grants them more action points at the cost of the action points gained in next turn in combat. \nTheir mobility on battlefield is enhanced by their talent &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;The Pawn&lt;/a&gt; which allows them 1 free action point worth of movement at the start of their turn in combat. Their ability to move around is further enhanced by their civil ability &lt;a href=\"Sneaking\"&gt;Sneaking&lt;/a&gt; which makes their movement around undetected easier. \nOut of all companions &lt;a href=\"Sebille%20Kaleran\"&gt;Sebille Kaleran&lt;/a&gt; is the one who chooses this specialisation by default.\nMercenary Pestilence.\nPestilence is an &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Lizards\"&gt;lizard&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be &lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Recruiting%20Mercenaries\"&gt;hired&lt;/a&gt; from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. His role on the battlefield is that of rogue, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Survivor%20classes\"&gt;survivor&lt;/a&gt; using &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scoundrel skills&lt;/a&gt; to decimate his foes.\nDetailed description.\nList of all skills available.\nRogue is a class focused on casting &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Scoundrel\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; skills. Following table shows all skills which Rogue can learn as they level up and invest points in respective combat ability."}
