{"id": "2820", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2820", "title": "Maxos", "text": "Maxos, the patriarch of &lt;a href=\"wizards\"&gt;wizards&lt;/a&gt; was once the greatest wizard in &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. In ancient times he was an ally to Emperor Sigurd and later ruled the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Tower\"&gt;Battle Tower&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island\"&gt;Sentinel Island&lt;/a&gt; before disappearing without a trace.\nBackground.\nHistorically, Maxos dedicated himself to the pursuit of knowledge above all else, specifically knowledge about &lt;a href=\"dragons\"&gt;dragons&lt;/a&gt;. At some point he was granted by the Ancient dragons an ability to grant the status of &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; to others. \nAround 8800 AR, Maxos was part of an alliance with Sigurd and The Architect to unite &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; under one empire in the name of peace. After this was accomplished and Sigurd named emperor, he witnessed Sigurd and The Architect become enemies over their mutual love for a dragon, and Sigurd's eventual death at the hands of his bastard children.\nMaxos was the one who originally hid the commander away as a child, to keep him from becoming corrupt as his half-siblings had. He had the Raven built around the demon &lt;a href=\"Corvus\"&gt;Corvus&lt;/a&gt;, and mentally imprisoned him there while stealing magical secrets from his mind. Eventually, he sought out the commander to train him and lead a revolution against the other royal bastards.\nAfter 8800 AR, Maxos partook in the event known as the Wizard Wars during which League of the Seven battled the League of the Damned. While Maxos refused to officially side with anyone during the Wizard Wars, he generally opposed the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;League of the Damned&lt;/a&gt; and their successors the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; as they acted as obstacles to his work, even nearly killing &lt;a href=\"Behrlihn\"&gt;Behrlihn&lt;/a&gt; twice. Moreso, Maxos accepted the role as the keeper of one of the keys to Behrlihns prison underneath &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;.\nShortly before 4 AR, Maxos imprisoned the rhyming wizard &lt;a href=\"Bellegar\"&gt;Bellegar&lt;/a&gt; in a cave near &lt;a href=\"Cyseal\"&gt;Cyseal&lt;/a&gt;. While not fully known, he is considered a legendary figure for mages who will sometimes invoke his name when casting spells. \nSeveral hundreds of years before 1218 AD, the wizard Maxos came to &lt;a href=\"Patriarch%20the%20Black\"&gt;Patriarch the Black&lt;/a&gt; and asked him to open a portal underneath the scorched desert of &lt;a href=\"Yuthul%20Gor\"&gt;Yuthul Gor&lt;/a&gt;. While Maxos claimed he wanted to enter the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Hall of Echoes&lt;/a&gt; for knowledge, Patriarch saw the truth, which Maxos wrote into his &lt;a href=\"Book%20of%20the%20Dragon\"&gt;Book of the Dragon&lt;/a&gt;; that Maxos wished to enter the Hall to surpass the Ancient dragons and gain power. \nWhether Maxos succeeded in his goal is not known, however it is implied he did manage to enter the Hall of Echoes and for whatever reason, abandoned his goal for power and locked his own Battle Tower through magic. Maxos had the tools he used to enter the Hall scattered and protected by various means. Afterwards he mysteriously disappeared.\n200 years, after his disappearance his Battle Tower was invaded by a necromancer &lt;a href=\"Laiken\"&gt;Laiken&lt;/a&gt;, who not only conquered it by sacrificing his lover &lt;a href=\"Sassan\"&gt;Sassan&lt;/a&gt;, but drove the Sentinel Island and its inhabitants to madness, through his cruelty. He was defeated by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the last Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD, after they had braved &lt;a href=\"Maxos%20Temple\"&gt;Maxos Temple&lt;/a&gt;, a place designed to train new Dragon Knights, that has been ruled by failed initiate &lt;a href=\"Amdusias\"&gt;Amdusias&lt;/a&gt; eversince Maxos soulforged Amdusias rival Lovis to his &lt;a href=\"Lovis%27%20Tower\"&gt;Tower&lt;/a&gt; and punished all who resided in the Temple regardless of their participation in the conflict. "}
