{"id": "10723", "revid": "53418829", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10723", "title": "Memory", "text": "Memory is an &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;attribute&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nMemory affects how many spells you can slot at a time. Only &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;spells/skills&lt;/a&gt; which have been slotted can be used, so Memory controls how many tactical options your character will have available, making this stat very important for spellcasters and less critical for melee fighters. \nThe base Memory amount is 10, as it is for all attributes. At 10 Memory a character will have 4 memory slots for spells/skills. \nEach point above 10 adds one more slot. For example, at 14 Memory, a character will have 8 slots: the 4 base slots plus 4 more slots for each point of Memory above 10. \nSkills and spells which are derived from equipment, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Races\"&gt;race&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;origin&lt;/a&gt; do not require a memory slot in order to be available for use. Only learned spells/skills must be slotted before using. Skills and spells may require 1, 2, or 3 memory slots each, depending on how advanced they are. "}
{"id": "8571", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8571", "title": "Memory Eater", "text": "Memory Eaters are large predatory creatures residing within &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Hall of Echoes&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nBackground.\nMemory Eaters are natural inhabitants of Hall of Echoes. Their role within the Hall is to purge the memories of the deceased souls in order to help them move unto next life or into the &lt;a href=\"Void\"&gt;Void&lt;/a&gt;. These spectral creatures are moving by flying or hovering and are large enough to threaten &lt;a href=\"dragons\"&gt;dragons&lt;/a&gt;. They can use their both their claws and magical attacks to defend themselves. As testified by &lt;a href=\"Charon\"&gt;Charon&lt;/a&gt; these creatures are intelligent enough to be capable of speech and may aid vengeful souls in their quest for revenge should a living person that wronged them enter the Hall of Echoes."}
{"id": "12324", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12324", "title": "Mend Metal", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;novice Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive geomancer skill that allows character to restore Physical Armour for both themselves and all their allies in 5 meter radius for 3 turns. Note that this skill does not increase the maximum amount of Physical Armour character has, only regenerates certain amount of it.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Earth%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Earth Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a novice Geomancer skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 4. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 100 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive skill whose effects depend on the following characteristics of the caster:\nOutside of the Level of the caster only their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; ability can influence the amount of Physical Armour restored by . \n properties can be affected by talents and other skills only. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Geomancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only &lt;a href=\"Gareth%20Pryce\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; throughout the game on &lt;a href=\"the%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;the Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;, provided their demands are met."}
{"id": "11229", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11229", "title": "Mendius", "text": "Mendius is a male &lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; found outside &lt;a href=\"King%20Crab%20Inn\"&gt;King Crab Inn&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Cyseal\"&gt;Cyseal&lt;/a&gt; in 4 AR.\nBackground.\nMendius is a member and recruiter in the Fabulous Five. He stands outside the door to the &lt;a href=\"King%20Crab%20Inn\"&gt;King Crab Inn&lt;/a&gt; in Cyseal and will speak to the Source Hunters as soon as he sees them. After asking a few questions he offers them a place in the Fabulous Five.\nIf the Source Hunters join the Fabulous Five he sends them to take out &lt;a href=\"Arhu\"&gt;Arhu&lt;/a&gt;'s rogue automaton, the SparkMaster 5000; Mayor &lt;a href=\"Cecil\"&gt;Cecil&lt;/a&gt; has offered a reward for its recovery or destruction. After returning to Cyseal, Mendius is nowhere to be found; speaking to Cecil reveals that he took the reward money and skipped town.\nMendius' dead body can later be found in the Immaculates' Trial Cave. A note on his body indicates he met &lt;a href=\"Loic\"&gt;Loic&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Silverglen\"&gt;Silverglen&lt;/a&gt; and got him to agree to his Fabulous Five scam so long as Mendius would join &lt;a href=\"Immaculates\"&gt;the Immaculates&lt;/a&gt;; it seems he entered the Corridor of Bane and was killed by rot."}
