{"id": "6038", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6038", "title": "Meteor Shower", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; skill in ' and '.\nDescription.\nOriginal Sin.\nSummon a veritable storm of fireballs from the sky. 8 fireballs come crashing from the sky. Each does X-Y fire damage to anything within a 2-meter range from impact. \n100% base chance to set \nCreates fire surfaces, melts ice surfaces, sets ooze and oil surfaces on fire.\nOriginal Sin Enhanced Edition.\n30 fireballs come crashing from the sky. Each does X-Y fire damage to entities within a 3.0m range from impact.\n100% chance to set Burning status for 3 turns."}
{"id": "10004", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10004", "title": "Meteor Shower (DOS EE)", "text": ""}
{"id": "12125", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12125", "title": "Meteor Shower (Original Sin 2)", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;master pyrokinetic source skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive pyrokinetic source skill that allows character to devastate chosen area (roughly 10 meter radius) with a meteor shower consisting of 25 meteors. Each meteor does fire damage, creates fire surface and damages all who are in 3 meter radius of the impact. Due to its nature, any flammable surfaces and clouds (oil, poison and web) will be set on fire and transformed into fire surface. \nCharacters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt; status due to the fire surface and suffer damage directly to their health. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;Pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 5 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 3 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 3000 gold. Since is a master Pyrokinetic skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 16.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have level and then Pyrokinetic ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Pyrokinetic).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist fire damage if they have: Fire Immunity Status and high enough Fire Resistance (which lowers fire damage done).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell pyrokinetic spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met."}
