{"id": "10962", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10962", "title": "Milk (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Milk is a &lt;a href=\"Consumables%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;consumable item&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a consumable item which may be used for cooking. When consumed it heals 10 % of maximum Vitality. Characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; are healed for 20 % of maximum Vitality. The effect of last 6 turns.\nPoisoned is a consumable item that was poisoned through various means (either &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Bottle%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;poison bottle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Zaikk%27s%20Talon\"&gt;Zaikk's Talon&lt;/a&gt;). Poisoning the will reduce its value to 0. Instead of healing it will deal poison damage equal to 10 % of the consumers maximum Vitality, rendering it unsafe for the living but safe for &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;. \nIf character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; the will deal poison damage equal to 20 % of the consumers maximum Vitality. The effect of last 6 turns. \nNote that poisoned item may be used in crafting, however the end product will be un-poisoned item.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of food and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for. "}
{"id": "15846", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15846", "title": "Milk and Honey", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Consumables\"&gt;consumable item&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a consumable item which may be used for cooking. When consumed it heals 15 % of maximum Vitality and grants + 20 % Poison Resistance as well as give &lt;a href=\"Warm%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Warm&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 2 turns. Characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; are healed for 30 % of maximum Vitality and granted + 40 % Poison Resistance. Talent has no effect on effectiveness or duration of the &lt;a href=\"Warm%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Warm&lt;/a&gt; status effect. The effect of last 6 turns.\nPoisoned is a consumable item that was poisoned through various means (either &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Bottle%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;poison bottle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Zaikk%27s%20Talon\"&gt;Zaikk's Talon&lt;/a&gt;). Poisoning the will reduce its value to 0. Instead of healing it will deal poison damage equal to 15 % of the consumers maximum Vitality, rendering it unsafe for the living but safe for &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; and granted + 20 % Poison Resistance as well as give &lt;a href=\"Warm%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Warm&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 2 turns. \nIf character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; the will deal poison damage equal to 30 % of the consumers maximum Vitality and granted + 40 % Poison Resistance. Talent has no effect on effectiveness or duration of the &lt;a href=\"Warm%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Warm&lt;/a&gt; status effect. The effect of last 6 turns. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of food and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs."}
