{"id": "12869", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12869", "title": "Mug of Beer", "text": "The mug of beer is a type of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Consumables%23Food%20and%20Drink\"&gt;drink&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a consumable item that, when consumed, will heal the consumers &lt;a href=\"Vitality\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; by 10%; however, it will also set the characters status to &lt;a href=\"Drunk%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Drunk&lt;/a&gt; and reduce their &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; by 1 point for 2 turns. Characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; are healed for 20 % of their Vitality while their Intelligence is reduced by 2 points. The &lt;a href=\"Drunk%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Drunk&lt;/a&gt; status effect remains unchanged. The effects of last 5 turns.\nPoisoned is a drink that was poisoned through various means (either &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Bottle%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;poison bottle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Zaikk%27s%20Talon\"&gt;Zaikk's Talon&lt;/a&gt;). Poisoning the will reduce its value to 0. Instead of healing it will deal poison damage equal to 10 % of the consumers maximum Vitality, rendering it unsafe for the living but safe for &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; and reduce their &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; by 1 point as well as applying &lt;a href=\"Drunk%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Drunk&lt;/a&gt; status effect. The effects of last 5 turns.\nIf character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; the will deal poison damage equal to 20 % of the consumers maximum Vitality and reduce their &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; by 2 points. The effects last 5 turns. \nNote that poisoned item may be used in crafting, however the end product will be un-poisoned item.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of food and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for. "}
