{"id": "18152", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18152", "title": "Mummie Dearest", "text": " is a mercenary of &lt;a href=\"the%20Lone%20Wolves\"&gt;the Lone Wolves&lt;/a&gt; residing at &lt;a href=\"Cullwoods%20Mill\"&gt;Cullwoods Mill&lt;/a&gt; in 1242 AD.\nBackground.\nRuthless mercenary and notorious murderess, Mummie Dearest is a criminal that is wanted throughout &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. Due to her actions, &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Order\"&gt;the Divine Order&lt;/a&gt; issued a reward on her head. She murdered &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Everhart\"&gt;Everhart&lt;/a&gt; as he and &lt;a href=\"Thom%20Hardwin\"&gt;Thom Hardwin&lt;/a&gt; were about to arrest her and has been hunted by him ever since. She is more deadly than the rest of the mercenaries with her only known weakness being water since it \"makes her itch\". She obtained her axe from recent raid on elven tribe and killed its previous owner with it."}
{"id": "2804", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2804", "title": "Mundus", "text": "Mundus is a cocky and reclusive mage living in the abandoned &lt;a href=\"High%20Hall%20Mines\"&gt;High Hall Mines&lt;/a&gt;, whose entrance is in northern area of &lt;a href=\"High%20Hall\"&gt;High Hall&lt;/a&gt; village in the &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nHe is rumored to have caused swarms of aggressive gnats to terrorize High Hall, and the villagers have since refused to trade with him because of it. &lt;a href=\"Quintus\"&gt;Quintus&lt;/a&gt; suspects that revenge is now motivating him to cause trouble in High Hall, and you receive the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Runes%20of%20Wrath\"&gt;The Runes of Wrath&lt;/a&gt; to take care of Mundus and the trolls that have been showing up around the village. Mundus shows disdain towards the villagers, calling them \"backwards peasants,\" but is willing to compromise if a method of acquiring food can be found that doesn't require him to deal with them again.\nMundus prefers runes of earth magic and takes great offense if you suggest that they are weak, which can be used to taunt him into attacking you.\n&lt;a href=\"Mundus%27%20Journal\"&gt;Mundus' Journal&lt;/a&gt; can be found on his table, and provides a little bit of information about the source of his ability to summon trolls."}
{"id": "8171", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8171", "title": "Mundus' Journal", "text": "Mundus' Journal is a &lt;a href=\"Books%20and%20notes%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; written by the mage &lt;a href=\"Mundus\"&gt;Mundus&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocation.\nFound on a table in his quarters in the &lt;a href=\"High%20Hall%20Mines\"&gt;High Hall Mines&lt;/a&gt;."}
