{"id": "8592", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8592", "title": "Nathirap and Eareb", "text": "Nathirap and Eareb are &lt;a href=\"goblin\"&gt;goblin&lt;/a&gt; brothers found in front of &lt;a href=\"Willy%27s%20House\"&gt;Willy's House&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Lanilor%20Lane\"&gt;Lanilor Lane&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; during the events of \"\".\nBackground.\nThey are warrior outcasts formerly known as the \"Brothers of the Spear,\" who relocated to Aleroth to live what Eareb calls \"a civilised life away from the tribes and backward shamans.\"\nThey were forced to surrender their weapons and take a vow to live like &lt;a href=\"humans\"&gt;humans&lt;/a&gt; upon arriving in Aleroth. To this end, they have tried experiencing all Aleroth has to offer, including visiting &lt;a href=\"Madame%20Eve%27s\"&gt;Madame Eve's&lt;/a&gt; regularly, although they don't quite seem to understand what occurs there (see \"&lt;a href=\"Madam%20Eve%27s%20Charter\"&gt;Madam Eve's Charter&lt;/a&gt;\").\nThe brothers have a strong dislike of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; and would like nothing more than to fight alongside the human &lt;a href=\"Champions\"&gt;Champions&lt;/a&gt;, but they have been shunned by &lt;a href=\"Aquila\"&gt;Captain Aquila&lt;/a&gt;. They offer the quest &lt;a href=\"Brothers%20in%20Arms\"&gt;Brothers in Arms&lt;/a&gt;, seeking your aid to be accepted.\nMap.\nLocation of Nathirap and Eareb (\"N\" on map - click image to enlarge):"}
