{"id": "17880", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17880", "title": "Nearby Depot", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDetailed Walkthrough.\nThe &lt;a href=\"letter%20from%20Pedro%20to%20Victorio\"&gt;letter from Pedro to Victorio&lt;/a&gt; give hints about the depot's whereabouts. Head down to the &lt;a href=\"Rivertown%20Sewers\"&gt;Rivertown Sewers&lt;/a&gt; and to the east you'll encounter &lt;a href=\"Pedro\"&gt;Pedro&lt;/a&gt; and some thugs, along with the stash.\nEither way, take the &lt;a href=\"Letter%20from%20Victorio%20to%20Pedro\"&gt;Letter from Victorio to Pedro&lt;/a&gt;.\nNotes.\nAt this point, if you've heard from Tingalf about the stash, It's safe to show the evidence first either to &lt;a href=\"Marcus\"&gt;Marcus&lt;/a&gt;, or to &lt;a href=\"Robin%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;Robin&lt;/a&gt;.\nDo note that;\nIf &lt;a href=\"Tingalf%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Tingalf (Quest)&lt;/a&gt; is still active when showing the evidence to Marcus, Tingalf disappears and &lt;a href=\"Tingalf%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Tingalf (Quest)&lt;/a&gt; becomes impossible to finish.\nShowing the evidence first to Robin, then to Marcus will make Tingalf to stay as merchant, even if you tell &lt;a href=\"Trevor\"&gt;Trevor&lt;/a&gt; about it.\nShowing evidence to Trevor requires informing Robin first.\nEither way, &lt;a href=\"Tingalf%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Tingalf (Quest)&lt;/a&gt; is easy to perma-lock at this stage.\nCompleting this quest also completes the journal entry The Black Market Depot."}
