{"id": "20222", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20222", "title": "Necrofire (Status)", "text": "Necrofire is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nNecrofire is a negative environmental effect that deals fire damage per turn and cannot be extinguished by normal means. Alongside the damage Necrofire will lower Fire Resistance by 20 % and grant Immunity to:\nCause.\nNecrofire can be caused by few ways on Rivellon. One of the simplest means is by casting &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; on \"fire surface\" or set fire to \"cursed oil surface\". There are few items and spells that allow setting enemies on Necrofire during combat. \nTreatment.\nNecrofire can be cancelled by three Status effects: &lt;a href=\"Blessed%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Blessed&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Fire%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Holy Fire&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Permafrost%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Permafrost&lt;/a&gt;. Other means of cancelling Necrofire include using &lt;a href=\"Spontaneous%20Combustion\"&gt;Spontaneous Combustion&lt;/a&gt; which will remove the effect, however it will increase fire damage done by it. If there are no viable means of cancelling Necrofire then the best way to endure it is by increasing Magic armour which is tied to &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Shell%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Magic Shell&lt;/a&gt; status.\nStatus negation.\nFollowing spells will completely cancel out Necrofire when casted."}
{"id": "16008", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16008", "title": "Necrofire Infusion", "text": "Necrofire Infusion is a &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning source skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive mixed source skill that allows caster to change their summoned Incarnate's element to necrofire. By changing the element, the Incarnate gains multiple boons associated with it. Its basic close attack will deal fire damage. Due to the Incarnate being infused with necrofire it gains Fire Resistance + 130 % but it will suffer from decreased resistance: Water Resistance - 20 %. Besides Fire resistance being increased the Incarnate becomes immune to &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Necrofire%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Necrofire&lt;/a&gt; status effects. Alongside this the Incarnate learns the Pyrokinetic skill &lt;a href=\"Fireball%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; and Pyrokinetic source skill &lt;a href=\"Epidemic%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Epidemic of Fire&lt;/a&gt; for which it also gains + 2 &lt;a href=\"Source%20Points%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Source Points&lt;/a&gt;. Lastly it will receive + 10 points to &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; ability itself. \nNote that unlike the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Infusion\"&gt;Fire Infusion&lt;/a&gt; the effects of cannot be achieved by summoning the Incarnate unto cursed fire surface.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;Pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into both &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted by combining any &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks out of which atleast one must be a source skillbook. Since is a mixed source skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from NPCs in the game.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift Bag: Pet Power allows this skill to be used on any summoned creature. This gift bag also shortens the cooldown of this skill from 3 turns to 1 turn. Following table shows what skills will specific summoned entity gain from . Note that there are no changes to the skill and bonuses granted by the skill to the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;, likewise all summoned entities gain source skill &lt;a href=\"Epidemic%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Epidemic of Fire&lt;/a&gt; and + 2 Source points."}
