{"id": "13153", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13153", "title": "Nemris", "text": "Nemris is an ancient author and philosopher who wrote the philosophy treatises \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Path%20of%20Life\"&gt;The Path of Life&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Philosophy%20of%20Death\"&gt;The Philosophy of Death&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBackground.\n\"Divine Divinity\".\nNemris, though long dead, still has a dedicated sect of followers in &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. At some point he set up a test in &lt;a href=\"Nericon%27s%20Garden\"&gt;Nericon's Garden&lt;/a&gt; where his spirit would inhabit a statue and test his pupils on his book \"The Path of Life\". Unfortunately for his followers, the garden was locked and &lt;a href=\"Blake\"&gt;Blake&lt;/a&gt; has the only key.\n\"Divinity: Original Sin\".\nNemris can be found buries in &lt;a href=\"Cyseal\"&gt;Cyseal&lt;/a&gt;'s cemetery. If the Source Hunters dig up his grave, his ghost will crawl out and introduce himself. He will offer to test their knowledge of his philosophy book \"The Philosophy of Death\"."}
{"id": "4103", "revid": "53418829", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4103", "title": "Nericon", "text": "Nericon is a powerful tree located in the &lt;a href=\"Mardaneus%20Plaza\"&gt;Mardaneus Plaza&lt;/a&gt; district of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nBefore making his appearance in Aleroth, Nericon was rumored to be an ancient &lt;a href=\"wizard\"&gt;wizard&lt;/a&gt; king who founded &lt;a href=\"Nericon%27s%20Garden\"&gt;Nericon's Garden&lt;/a&gt; on the ground previously occupied by common people's houses, which he ordered to be torn down. Nericon was known to have close ties with nature and possesses an ability to inhabit plants to intervene in the world personally.\nThe Dragon Knight first meets Nericon on Mardaneus Plaza when he, in form of a tree, strikes lightning on undead and an unfortunate &lt;a href=\"champions\"&gt;champion&lt;/a&gt; Bubo who tried to pass around it. The Knight tried to communicate with the tree but it was for naught as the tree spoke only in ancient Elven language. Unable to speak with him, the Knight headed to &lt;a href=\"Prancing%20Seahorse\"&gt;Prancing Seahorse&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Lanilor%20Lane\"&gt;Lanilor Lane&lt;/a&gt; to obtain a book titled \"&lt;a href=\"Elven%20Alphabet\"&gt;Elven Alphabet&lt;/a&gt;\" in Forbidden Archives.\nAfter gaining an ability to speak ancient elven language the Knight learned from Nericon that he is dedicated to destroy the taint of &lt;a href=\"Creatures%23Undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; that plague the city. Therefore he appeared on the Mardaneus Plaza to serve as a barrier against the dead and alive. Only the Knight after stating their intention to destroy this evil was allowed to pass unharmed."}
{"id": "18168", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18168", "title": "Nericon's Garden", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20Locations\"&gt;garden&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nLocated east of the &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Abbey\"&gt;Cursed Abbey&lt;/a&gt;, the garden was built by a wizard named &lt;a href=\"Nericon\"&gt;Nericon&lt;/a&gt;.\nDuring the Age of Deception, &lt;a href=\"Rivertown\"&gt;Rivertown&lt;/a&gt; was ruled by Nericon. He decided that Rivertown would be the site for the most magnificent garden in &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. The site where he was going to build the garden was inhabited by the poor people of Rivertown. To minimize the fuzz with supporters, he had palace guards drive the poor out of their homes and burn the houses and shacks.\nAfter this, slaves built Nericon's garden, which would act as both garden and as a treasure vault. \nLayout.\nThe garden doors are locked, but &lt;a href=\"Blake\"&gt;Blake&lt;/a&gt; has the key, and is willing to part with it provided &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; has a good reputation. The garden is fenced in all around.\nInside the garden are plenty of different plants and a few statues. Killing all frogs in the vicinity opens a secret portal to the treasure vault.\nIn the treasure vault a door can be opened with a lever hidden behind the boxes."}
{"id": "3834", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3834", "title": "Nericon's Wrath", "text": "Nericon's Wrath is a &lt;a href=\"Flames%20of%20Vengeance%20quests\"&gt;main quest&lt;/a&gt; received from &lt;a href=\"Nericon\"&gt;Nericon&lt;/a&gt;, the magical tree in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". The tree kills passers-by indiscriminately on the &lt;a href=\"Creatures%23Undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;-infested side of the barrier dividing &lt;a href=\"Mardaneus%20Plaza\"&gt;Mardaneus Plaza&lt;/a&gt;. This quest is assigned when it allows &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; to pass, permitting access to the city's &lt;a href=\"Crow%27s%20Nest\"&gt;Crow's Nest&lt;/a&gt; district.\nDetailed Walkthrough.\nPrerequisites.\nComplete &lt;a href=\"Seahorse%20Salad\"&gt;Seahorse Salad&lt;/a&gt; to obtain the &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Alphabet\"&gt;Elven Alphabet&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Books%20and%20notes%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt;, then &lt;a href=\"Bark%20up%20the%20Right%20Tree\"&gt;Bark up the Right Tree&lt;/a&gt; to be allowed to pass Nericon unharmed.\nWalkthrough.\nHead into the Crow's Nest and find the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Crypt\"&gt;Forgotten Crypt&lt;/a&gt; at the end of the first street.\n&lt;a href=\"Skulk\"&gt;Skulk&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"troll\"&gt;troll&lt;/a&gt; will greet you inside. &lt;a href=\"Mindread\"&gt;Mindread&lt;/a&gt; him for 15000 &lt;a href=\"exp\"&gt;exp&lt;/a&gt; to hear him chant some strange words. If you mindread Skulk every time you meet, you will be able to disable the trap on the &lt;a href=\"Source%20Square\"&gt;Source Square&lt;/a&gt; door without sacrificing Abbott. Make your way through the fire and pull the lever to open the door. Skulk will appear to taunt you again. Follow him through the next set of traps and pull the next lever. When you get to the next door, pull the lever to open it.\nJump onto the platforms to avoid the poison and pull the lever on the third platform. Jump down and head through the unlocked door to meet &lt;a href=\"Abbott\"&gt;Abbott&lt;/a&gt;.\nFollow Abbott out of the room and head to the other door which was previously locked. Skulk will appear again, and a dialog will ensue with Abbott in which he declares there is no way to get past the deadly trap on the door without sacrificing himself. Choose what to do to get the door open. (If you've mindread Skulk each time you've spoken to him, then you don't have to sacrifice Abbott, he can cast the spell that Skulk was thinking of.)\nHead into &lt;a href=\"Source%20Square\"&gt;Source Square&lt;/a&gt;. Go up the stairs and down the hall and the &lt;a href=\"Engineer\"&gt;Engineer&lt;/a&gt; will appear. You will be shown a cutscene and &lt;a href=\"Behrlihn\"&gt;Behrlihn&lt;/a&gt; will offer a hint at what you need to do. There is no specific order to pulling the levers. Once all of the devices are deactivated and the minions are dead, battle the Engineer and loot the &lt;a href=\"Engineer%27s%20Sword\"&gt;Engineer's Sword&lt;/a&gt; for Clue IV of &lt;a href=\"To%20Find%20a%20Wizard\"&gt;To Find a Wizard&lt;/a&gt; following his death. Return to Nericon."}
{"id": "8640", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8640", "title": "Nerk", "text": "Nerk can be found standing guard outside the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Market\"&gt;Black Market&lt;/a&gt; trapdoor on &lt;a href=\"Lanilor%20Lane\"&gt;Lanilor Lane&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; (near the &lt;a href=\"Playhouse\"&gt;Playhouse&lt;/a&gt; &amp; across the road from &lt;a href=\"Madame%20Eve%27s\"&gt;Madame Eve's&lt;/a&gt;) in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nHe is a merchant, selling stolen &lt;a href=\"Armour%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"shields\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; quietly on the street. He gets aggravated if asked about the trapdoor."}
{"id": "8901", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8901", "title": "Nerus", "text": "Nerus is a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; agent posing as a &lt;a href=\"champions\"&gt;champion&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nHe is first seen during a brief encounter at the &lt;a href=\"Circle%20of%20Trust%20Inn\"&gt;Circle of Trust Inn&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Mardaneus%20Plaza\"&gt;Mardaneus Plaza&lt;/a&gt;, where he quickly recognizes the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; and excuses himself before leaving.\nHe is later revealed to be a traitor working for the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt;, and is witnessed killing his fellow conspirator, &lt;a href=\"Kenzo\"&gt;Kenzo&lt;/a&gt;, near the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Crow%27s%20Nest\"&gt;Crow's Nest&lt;/a&gt; district before fleeing the scene.\nNerus is met again near the Crow's Nest waypoint shrine. When confronted, he reveals that he has acquired an ancient &lt;a href=\"Maxos\"&gt;Maxos&lt;/a&gt; magic spell, and plans to flood Aleroth with legions of the &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Damned One's&lt;/a&gt; troops to take down the city from within. It is too late to prevent him from casting it, and eventually the spell takes effect. Unfortunately for Nerus, the spell falls short of an inundation of troops, with only three Black Ring members being teleported to the site. You must fight Nerus and the three Black Ring members (level 39) simultaneously. To simplify the battle, focus on killing the healer first."}
{"id": "15729", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15729", "title": "Nesta Bartram", "text": "Nesta Bartram is a &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt; stationed at &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20Checkpoint\"&gt;Paladin Checkpoint&lt;/a&gt; in 1242 AD."}
{"id": "12189", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12189", "title": "Nether Swap", "text": "Nether Swap is an &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;adept Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive aerotheurge skill that allows caster to make two characters (or corpses) swap positions (the chosen target character can be caster themselves). Note that it is not possible to teleport a character affected by &lt;a href=\"Fortified%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Fortified&lt;/a&gt; status effect or if they are immune to Teleportation in general.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurgy\"&gt;Aerotheurgy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Air%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Air Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is an adept Aerotheurge skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 9.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 260 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive aerotheurge skill that allows caster to teleport characters and as such it is not affected by the Level, Aerotheurge ability and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; attribute of the caster.\nHowever the skill itself can still be affected by other skills and talents.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell hydrosophist spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met. Also note that &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Dreamer\"&gt;Lizard Dreamer&lt;/a&gt; requires a persuasion check to be passed in order to speak with him, otherwise he (and the whole encampment) will turn hostile. "}
