{"id": "20101", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20101", "title": "Oil Infusion", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive mixed skill that allows caster to change their summoned Incarnate's element to earth. By changing the element, the Incarnate gains multiple boons associated with it. Its basic close attack will deal earth damage. Due to the Incarnate being infused with earth it gains Earth Resistance + 120 % but it suffer from decreased resistances: Air Resistance - 20 %. Besides Earth resistance being increased the Incarnate becomes immune to &lt;a href=\"Petrified%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Petrified&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Slowed%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Slowed&lt;/a&gt; status effects. Alongside this the Incarnate learns the Geomancer skill &lt;a href=\"Fossil%20Strike\"&gt;Fossil Strike&lt;/a&gt;. Lastly it will receive + 5 points to Geomancer ability itself.\nThe effects of are achieved by summoning the Incarnate unto any oil surface. Note that this skill is part of the feature Pet Power and it is not present in the game as a craftable/usable skill unless the feature has been manually activated.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from NPCs in the game.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift Bag: Pet Power allows this skill to be used on any summoned creature. This gift bag also shortens the cooldown of this skill from 3 turns to 1 turn. Following table shows what skills will specific summoned entity gain from . Note that there are no changes to the skill and bonuses granted by the skill to the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;."}
