{"id": "16929", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16929", "title": "Old Cave", "text": " is a dungeon in north west of &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley%20Village\"&gt;Broken Valley Village&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nA cave that has stood for aeons, it is now the home of &lt;a href=\"Naberius\"&gt;Naberius&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nUpon entering the cave there is a portcullis at the end of the passage, passing through leads into the living area. Immediately ahead against the door is chest and turning left a piano can be seen the far end. Moving into the centre of the room, a locked box can be seen in the front left corner, the key to which is located in the bathtub on the right. To the left is a chest and to right a further two more. Walking to the piano and turning right is another doorway. Follow the passage to the rear and in the centre of the room is a necromancy ring, with its owner, Naberius behind it. Behind Naberius there is scaffoldiing installed."}
{"id": "4062", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4062", "title": "Old Dog or New Tricks?", "text": "Old Dog or New Tricks? is a &lt;a href=\"Flames%20of%20Vengeance%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; offered by the Champion &lt;a href=\"Messalina\"&gt;Messalina&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Circle%20of%20Trust%20Inn\"&gt;Circle of Trust Inn&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Mardaneus%20Plaza\"&gt;Mardaneus Plaza&lt;/a&gt; district of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; during the events of \"\". \nDetailed Walkthrough.\nMessalina explains that she has sent two Champions, &lt;a href=\"Aulus\"&gt;Aulus&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Minius\"&gt;Minius&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Nimir\"&gt;Temple of Nimir&lt;/a&gt;, and is upset that they've been gone so long for what should be \"a simple cleanup mission.\" She isn't concerned for their safety, she simply wants you to tell them to hurry up.\nSimply walk to the &lt;a href=\"Prancing%20Seahorse\"&gt;Prancing Seahorse&lt;/a&gt;, across the road from &lt;a href=\"Luxurius%27%20Mansion\"&gt;Luxurius' Mansion&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Lanilor%20Lane\"&gt;Lanilor Lane&lt;/a&gt;. You'll find the pair outside, arguing about who should go into the temple. It seems that Aulus thinks that Minius isn't experienced enough, and Minius thinks that Aulus is too old. Neither one wants to the other to die at the hands of the &lt;a href=\"Creatures%23Undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;, and they ask you to decide who should go. You can &lt;a href=\"mindread\"&gt;mindread&lt;/a&gt; Aulus for 7500 &lt;a href=\"exp\"&gt;exp&lt;/a&gt; to discover that he is hiding an injury. This adds a dialogue choice but doesn't effect the outcome.\nIf Minius is sent to the Temple of Nimir:\nIf Aulus is sent to the Temple of Nimir:\nWhoever is not chosen expresses concern for their colleague, then walks to the &lt;a href=\"Phoenix%20Inn\"&gt;Phoenix Inn&lt;/a&gt;. They can be found there, enjoying ale for the remainder of the game.\nAfter making your decision, return to Messalina at the Circle of Trust Inn and explain what happened to complete the quest."}
