{"id": "10970", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10970", "title": "Watermelon", "text": "' is a type of &lt;a href=\"Consumables%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Food%20and%20Drink\"&gt;food&lt;/a&gt; in '.\nCharacteristics.\n is a consumable item which will heal 5 % of maximum Vitality and grant + 10 % Fire Resistance upon consuming. If character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; it will heal 10 % of maximum Vitality and grant + 20 % Fire Resistance. The effect of last 3 turns.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of food and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs."}
{"id": "2146", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2146", "title": "Watermill", "text": "The watermill is a building in &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley%20Village\"&gt;Broken Valley Village&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nPart of the village's self sustenance, the mill has been run by &lt;a href=\"Upton\"&gt;Upton&lt;/a&gt; since 1230 AD as a cover for his alchemic pursuits with &lt;a href=\"Abanayabar\"&gt;Abanayabar&lt;/a&gt;. Although the milling itself is done by Upton, his daughter &lt;a href=\"Linda\"&gt;Linda&lt;/a&gt; collects the grain from &lt;a href=\"Jackson%27s%20farm\"&gt;Jackson's farm&lt;/a&gt;, with &lt;a href=\"Peavey\"&gt;Peavey&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Quincy\"&gt;Quincy&lt;/a&gt; providing armed guard.\nLayout.\nEntering from the northeast entrance of the mill, close to the village's exterior wall and adjacent to the river, the ground floor consists of the stairs to the first floor on the right, the grind stones in the centre and a locked gate to the right hand side. Beyond this gate is the hatch down to the basement.\nTravelling up the stairs to the first floor, the living area can be found, with both miller Upton and Linda found here. The bedroom is through the archway to the right of the stairs, where &lt;a href=\"The%20Ballard%20of%20Jack%20Miller\"&gt;The Ballard of Jack Miller&lt;/a&gt; and Linda (when she is not in the main living area) can be found on the furthest bed. Between the two beds is an unlocked chest. On the wall opposite the beds is the second entry to the mill, leading out to south side of the building.\nLeaving the bedroom back to the main living area, just beyond the stairs is an unlocked chest, with the kitchen is behind this. On the kitchen counters there are three loaves of &lt;a href=\"bread\"&gt;bread&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"honey%20pot\"&gt;honey pot&lt;/a&gt; in the corner of the counter by the stove. In the kettle to the right of the counter is the key to the locked gate on the ground floor (either Upton must be mindread or &lt;a href=\"Stan\"&gt;Stan&lt;/a&gt; spoken to after the quest &lt;a href=\"Band%20of%20Brutes\"&gt;Band of Brutes&lt;/a&gt; for it to appear in the original release of \"Ego Draconis\") among the 4 lettuces; below the lettuces is single &lt;a href=\"apple\"&gt;apple&lt;/a&gt;. Immediately in front of the pot is the grain hatch that feeds into the millstones. Looking to the right of the counter tops is another ledge further splitting the living area with a further 7 loaves of bread. Beyond this ledge, Upton can found sitting at the large round table, which has a &lt;a href=\"pear\"&gt;pear&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"tomato\"&gt;tomato&lt;/a&gt;es upon it. Turning right again there is cupboard directly ahead with a candlestick on top, a table with a small box on top of it to the left and a locked chest between the table and the cupboard.\nHeading back down the stairs and through the locked gate a &lt;a href=\"ginseng\"&gt;ginseng&lt;/a&gt; can be found on shelf next to hatch down to the basement. In the basement itself is a passageway with plants running the length of it. Immediately on the left a &lt;a href=\"fanny%20blossom\"&gt;fanny blossom&lt;/a&gt; and 2 &lt;a href=\"whisperwood\"&gt;whisperwood&lt;/a&gt; plants and &lt;a href=\"oak%20tears\"&gt;oak tears&lt;/a&gt; can be taken from the pots. On the table to the far right the formula for the &lt;a href=\"potion%20of%20lesser%20revitalising\"&gt;potion of lesser revitalising&lt;/a&gt; can be found; the opposite table has the formula for the &lt;a href=\"potion%20of%20lesser%20healing\"&gt;potion of lesser healing&lt;/a&gt; and a fatfern. Passing through the doorway at the end of the passage leads into the main chamber with &lt;a href=\"Abanayabar\"&gt;Abanayabar&lt;/a&gt; dominating the far end. at the point in the entryway to the chamber a &lt;a href=\"holy%20basil\"&gt;holy basil&lt;/a&gt; on the right and a &lt;a href=\"whisperwood\"&gt;whisperwood&lt;/a&gt; to the can be found, an iron ore vein can be seen on the left and &lt;a href=\"fatfern\"&gt;fatfern&lt;/a&gt; to the right of where the entry meets the chamber. Continuing toward Abanayabar, by the last pot on the left a &lt;a href=\"black%20rose\"&gt;black rose&lt;/a&gt; can be found with another ginseng. \nVeering to the left, it is possible to head behind Abanayabar. Here is scaffolding with a set of stairs up to the first level, to the right of the stairs, just under the scaffolding is another fatfern. Heading up the steps and turning left to follow the platform around a locked chest can be found at the end that can be opened with 3 points in &lt;a href=\"Lockpick\"&gt;Lockpick&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "11329", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11329", "title": "Waters", "text": "Waters is a &lt;a href=\"Magister\"&gt;Magister&lt;/a&gt; on board the \"&lt;a href=\"Merryweather\"&gt;Merryweather&lt;/a&gt;\" in 1242 AD.\nBackground.\nWaters is a magister investigating murder of the &lt;a href=\"Sourcerer\"&gt;Sourcerer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Finn\"&gt;Finn&lt;/a&gt;. She is angry that it happened while she was guarding sleeping and freshly collared &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "3607", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3607", "title": "Way of the Battle Mage", "text": "Way of the Battle Mage is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Mage\"&gt;Mage skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nWay of the Battle Mage is a active Mage skill that allows the Knight to temporarily boost their Magic Damage whilst lowering Magic Armour and Indomitable Will. The penalty to Magic Armour and Indomitable Will persists until 5th level of the skill, after which the penalty will turn into bonus to those values. \nThis skill can be cast with any weapon in hand.\nCan be canceled at any time, cooldown starts after the duration ends or after it is manually turned off.\nThe following are mutually exclusive, only one can be active: &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Battle%20Mage\"&gt;Way of the Battle Mage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Wise%20Wizard\"&gt;Way of the Wise Wizard&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Ranger\"&gt;Way of the Ranger&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Rage\"&gt;Battle Rage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Posture\"&gt;Defensive Posture&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3609", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3609", "title": "Way of the Ranger", "text": "Way of the Ranger is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Ranger\"&gt;Ranger skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nWay of the Ranger is a active Ranger skill that allows the Knight to temporarily increase their physical damage (not magic damage), ranged armour and heightened reflexes at the cost of melee armour and melee damage. This skill can be cast with any weapon in hands.\nNote: Bow damage is the base bow damage, not a bonus to bow damage.\u00a0 Level 1 lets the player attack for 114% of their base damage; it does not add 114% more ranged damage.\nNote: The Bow Damage bonus ONLY applied to physical damage; magic damage (blue number in parentheses) on the character sheet will not be increased.\nCan be canceled at any time, cooldown starts after the duration ends or after it is manually turned off.\nThe following are mutually exclusive, only one can be active: &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Battle%20Mage\"&gt;Way of the Battle Mage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Wise%20Wizard\"&gt;Way of the Wise Wizard&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Ranger\"&gt;Way of the Ranger&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Rage\"&gt;Battle Rage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Posture\"&gt;Defensive Posture&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3605", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3605", "title": "Way of the Wise Wizard", "text": "Way of the Wise Wizard is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Priest\"&gt;Priest skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nWay of the Wise Wizard is a active Priest skill that allows the Knight to temporarily increase their Magic Armour and Indomitable Will at the cost of Magic Damage. The penalty to Magic Damage persists until 12th level of the skill, after which the penalty will turn into bonus to those values. This bonus is not just for spells, it also includes the magic damage (blue number in parentheses) on all melee and ranged &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;. This skill can be cast with any weapon in hands.\nCan be canceled at any time, cooldown starts after the duration ends or after it is manually turned off.\nThe following are mutually exclusive, only one can be active: &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Battle%20Mage\"&gt;Way of the Battle Mage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Wise%20Wizard\"&gt;Way of the Wise Wizard&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Ranger\"&gt;Way of the Ranger&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Rage\"&gt;Battle Rage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Posture\"&gt;Defensive Posture&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5057", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5057", "title": "Wayfarer (Original Sin)", "text": "Wayfarer is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%20Classes\"&gt;survivor class&lt;/a&gt; in ' and the '.\nBackground.\nThe wayfarer was not born of woman, but of beast...or so the rumours go. Raised by the creatures and trees of the &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20Forest\"&gt;Phantom Forest&lt;/a&gt;, the wayfarer learned the art of survival before that of speech.\nBeasts that would have destroyed another human in a single swipe were the Wayfarer's caretakers and playmates; dodging lightning storms, a matter of survival for most, was the wayfarer's favourite sport.\nWhen the Grandmaster of the Order of the &lt;a href=\"Source%20Hunter\"&gt;Source Hunter&lt;/a&gt;s learned of this remarkable person, he ordered an expedition to make contact. Though wary of leaving the wilds, the wayfarer was eager to learn more about these strange but powerful Source Hunters.\nStarting Statistics.\nFollowing table shows all statistics, spells and items of the Wayfarer at the start of the game. There are no major differences between \"Classic\" and \"Enhanced\" versions of the game save for few minor changes in stats, abilities, skills and items at their disposal. \nIn Enhanced Edition the Wayfarer has 1 additional point in Dexterity which was taken from Intelligence (Dexterity has therefore 2 points and Intelligence 1 point invested). Their skills &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Heal\"&gt;Minor Heal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Magical%20Poison%20Dart\"&gt;Magical Poison Dart&lt;/a&gt; (in Classic Edition) got replaced with &lt;a href=\"First%20Aid%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;First Aid&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ricochet\"&gt;Ricochet&lt;/a&gt; skills. Their ability to wield &lt;a href=\"Bow\"&gt;Bow&lt;/a&gt; got replaced with &lt;a href=\"Crossbow%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Crossbow&lt;/a&gt; ability. Following this their weapon &lt;a href=\"Source%20Hunter%27s%20Bow\"&gt;Source Hunter's Bow&lt;/a&gt; was replaced with &lt;a href=\"Light%20Old%20Crossbow\"&gt;Light Old Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;. Another difference is that instead of 1 Minor Healing potion they have 2 Minor Healing potions and their &lt;a href=\"Immune%20to%20Poisoning\"&gt;Immune to Poisoning scroll&lt;/a&gt; got replaced with &lt;a href=\"Oil%20Flask\"&gt;Oil Flask&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "10594", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10594", "title": "Wayfarer (Original Sin 2)", "text": "The Wayfarer is a &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;survivor class&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nSummary.\nWayfarer is a survivor specialising in &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; magic and &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; skill. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. Their primary weapons are crossbows and bows. \nThe Wayfarers first starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Arrowheads\"&gt;Elemental Arrowheads&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to adapt their damage type according to nearby surfaces. Their second starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Pin%20Down\"&gt;Pin Down&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to not only damage their foe but also immobilise them. The third final starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Fossil%20Strike\"&gt;Fossil Strike&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to hurl a chunk of earth at their enemies and create an oil surface beneath them. \nTheir civil skill is &lt;a href=\"Bartering%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Bartering&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to haggle better prices when dealing with Merchants. Their talent is &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Pet Pal&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to speak to animals.\nOut of all companions &lt;a href=\"Ifan%20ben-Mezd\"&gt;Ifan ben-Mezd&lt;/a&gt; is the one who chooses this specialisation by default. \nMercenary Morrgen.\nMorrgen is an &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be &lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Recruiting%20Mercenaries\"&gt;hired&lt;/a&gt; from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. His role on the battlefield is that of wayfarer, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Survivor%20classes\"&gt;survivor&lt;/a&gt; using &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman skills&lt;/a&gt; in combination with &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer magic&lt;/a&gt; to defeat his enemies.\nDetailed description.\nList of all skills available.\nWayfarer is a class focused on casting &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; spells. Following table shows all skills and spells which Wayfarer can learn as they level up and invest points in respective combat abilities."}
