{"id": "8625", "revid": "37013771", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8625", "title": "West", "text": "Dr. West is a doctor residing in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nDr. West is a medical doctor, mortician, and &lt;a href=\"necromancer\"&gt;necromancer&lt;/a&gt; at the mortuary in the basement of the &lt;a href=\"Circle%20of%20Trust%20Inn\"&gt;Circle of Trust Inn&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Mardaneus%20Plaza\"&gt;Mardaneus Plaza&lt;/a&gt; district of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; during the events of \"\". A self-described \"limb-lacerating puppeteer,\" his morbid knowledge proves useful during the quest &lt;a href=\"Murders%20in%20the%20Rue%20Lanilor\"&gt;Murders in the Rue Lanilor&lt;/a&gt;.\nDr. West takes joy in the outbreak of walking dead in the city, seeing it as an excellent opportunity for research, which he hopes will earn respect at the &lt;a href=\"Prancing%20Seahorse\"&gt;Prancing Seahorse&lt;/a&gt; and increase his standing with &lt;a href=\"Deodatus\"&gt;Deodatus&lt;/a&gt;. He also mentions rumors of secret rooms and experimentation at the &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Willows%20Manor\"&gt;Wild Willows Manor&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Crow%27s%20Nest\"&gt;Crow's Nest&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "16913", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16913", "title": "West Valley Shrine", "text": ""}
{"id": "20218", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20218", "title": "Wet (Status)", "text": "Wet is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nWet is an environmental status effect applied whenever character comes into contact with water surface such as puddles, rivers, lakes etc. It is one of the few status effects that is applied regardless of Armour, Resistances or Immunities. Whenever character is Wet they will suffer from decreased water resistance by 10 % and decreased air resistance by 20 %, however their fire resistance will be increased by 10 %. \nCause.\nThere are many ways through which wet status effect can be triggered. On &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; it is the contact with \"water surface\" or most notably entering &lt;a href=\"Stonegarden\"&gt;Stonegarden&lt;/a&gt; where it rains most of the time. In combat Wet status can be triggered by items or by &lt;a href=\"Rain\"&gt;Rain&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;hydrosophist spell&lt;/a&gt;. \nTreatment.\nWet is one of the few status effect that is applied regardless of Armour, Resistances or Immunities. The only way it can be treated is through anything that causes &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning status&lt;/a&gt; which will turn Wet status into &lt;a href=\"Warm%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Warm status&lt;/a&gt;. One of the ways to achieve this is by coming into contact with \"fire surface\" or \"fire cloud\"."}
