{"id": "10079", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10079", "title": "Whirlwind (Original Sin)", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Man-at-Arms%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Man-at Arms skill&lt;/a&gt; in ' and '.\nOriginal Sin.\nDescription.\nPerform a whirlwind attack, hitting enemies around you for 120% weapon damage.\nEnhanced Edition.\nDescription.\nPerform a whirlwind attack, hitting enemies around you for 90% weapon damage.\nTip.\nThe skill description of Whirlwind does not reflect the bonus from high STR (above 10), while higher strength DOES give higher damage. Thus the actual damage is usually higher than indicated in-game. Whirlwind can crit or miss."}
{"id": "11373", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11373", "title": "Whirlwind (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Whirlwind is a &lt;a href=\"Warfare%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;novice Warfare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive warfare skill that allows caster to whirl around and attack all their enemies around them simultaneously in one turn.\nSince requires a weapon it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Atrophy%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Atrophy&lt;/a&gt; status effect.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. Since is a novice Warfare skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 4.\nSince is a weapon based skill and as such it does not have a scroll. It is also not possible to craft a skillbook.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus %) x (1 + Attribute Bonus % + Weapon Skill Bonus % + Misc Bonuses % ) x (1 + High Ground Bonus % + Crit Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Compatible attribute provides the lowest bonus out of the three (example: 3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Pyrokinetic).\nNote that the reach of this skill depends on the range of the weapon itself. Note that the range of the weapon does not equal the range of the skill. All the melee weapons in the table have fixed range safe for one-handed swords, axes and maces where the range oscilates between 4 meters and 4.4 meters depending on direction from the caster.\n properties (except range) can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills.\nLocations.\nCreatures and NPCs.\nFollowing table shows all creatures and NPCs which have a chance to drop the item upon death. Highlighted creatures in this table have 100 % chance to drop said item. Note that creatures may drop other items as well.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell warfare skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Gareth\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if his demands are met."}
{"id": "4936", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4936", "title": "Whisperwood", "text": "Whisperwood is a herb found throughout &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". \nDescription.\nIt is used primarily for crafting armor / resistance &lt;a href=\"potions\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt;. Whisperwood can be harvested from plants, and is sometimes sold by merchants, found as random loot, or received as a quest reward. Later in the game, it can also be easily obtained by assigning Harry, one of the &lt;a href=\"runners\"&gt;runners&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Tower\"&gt;Battle Tower&lt;/a&gt; to collect it."}
{"id": "11810", "revid": "24816040", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11810", "title": "Whisperwood (Original Sin 2)", "text": "The is a type of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Consumables%23Plants\"&gt;herb&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nWhisperwood is a herb that can be found freely growing on &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. When consumed it will increase Magic Armour by 2 points for the duration of 2 turns. If character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; the herb will increase Magic Armour by 3 points for the duration of 2 turns.\nDistinctive Whisperwood is a rare type of Whisperwood which can only be grown from &lt;a href=\"Whisperwood%20Seedling\"&gt;Whisperwood Seedling&lt;/a&gt;s placed upon oil surface. When consumed it will increase Magic Armour by 2 points for the duration of 2 turns like its base counterpart. If character has Five-Star Diner talent the herb will increase Magic Armour by 3 points for the duration of 2 turns. Note that in order to grow this herb and buy it the player must have activated Gift Bag: Herb Gardens.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of herbs and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs."}
{"id": "17643", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17643", "title": "Whisperwood Seedling", "text": "Whisperwood Seedling is a type of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20miscellaneous%20items\"&gt;miscellaneous item&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nA bucket with growing &lt;a href=\"Whisperwood%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Whisperwood&lt;/a&gt; seedling. Place it unto ground for it to begin growing. After 2 turns the seedling will grow into harvestable herb which produces random amount of Whisperwood, ranging from 1 to 3 herbs. Note that placing whisperwood seedling unto oil surface grants a large chance to produce Distinctive Whisperwood.\nAfter harvesting the herb the &lt;a href=\"Bucket\"&gt;Bucket&lt;/a&gt; used will become &lt;a href=\"Clay-filled%20bucket\"&gt;Clay-filled bucket&lt;/a&gt;."}
