{"id": "9794", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9794", "title": "Wind-Up Toy (DOS EE)", "text": ""}
{"id": "12423", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12423", "title": "Wind-Up Toy (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Wind-up toy is a &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;master Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nSummon a mechanical bomber at the target point with the &lt;a href=\"Suicide%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Suicide&lt;/a&gt; skill. The bomber will explode upon death or expiration, dealing fire damage and producing a fire surface.\nDoes not break Invisibility or Sneaking.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Scoundrel\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 1400 gold. Since is a master Scoundrel skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 16.\nSince is a weapon based skill and as such it does not have a scroll. It is also not possible to craft a skillbook.\nSkill Modifiers.\nScales off caster level and &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; ability.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell scoundrel skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift bag: Pet Power allows the player to infuse not only their Incarnate but also all other summoned creatures. This includes the \"Wind-up Toy\" as well. Note that skills gained by infusing it, may differ from skills gained by infusing other summoned creatures.\nElemental Infusions.\nInfusing Wind-Up Toy with elemental infusions will cause it to create a corresponding elemental surface at its death or expiration. The only exception are Oil amd Poison infusions which will become a fire surface due to the explosion of the Wind-Up Toy. Electric infusion also leaves an electrified steam cloud. Unlike the rest of the summoned creatures, infusions here do not provide new skills and instead change the elemental property of the already owned skill &lt;a href=\"Suicide%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Suicide&lt;/a&gt;."}
