{"id": "3661", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3661", "title": "Wisdom (Dragon Knight Saga)", "text": "Wisdom is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Dragon%20Slayer\"&gt;Dragon Slayer skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in .\nDescription.\nWisdom is a passive \"Dragon Slayer skill\" that increases experience gained from slaying enemies and solving quests. Due to its nature it is always in effect. \nNotes.\nAs with the &lt;a href=\"Mindread\"&gt;Mindread&lt;/a&gt; skill, Wisdom can help you earn more experience. Keep in mind, however, that the experience rewarded per kill in \"Divinity II\" is dependent on both the character's level and the enemy's level. The higher your level, the lower your experience gain will be for killing any given enemy, and vice versa. Due to this mechanic, leveling quickly may not always be desirable, and experience-enhancing skills can be less useful than their raw bonuses suggest."}
{"id": "4585", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4585", "title": "Wisdom in a Bottle", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDetailed Walkthrough.\nWisdom in a Bottle is the second quest assigned by &lt;a href=\"Allan%20%28Sentinel%20Island%29\"&gt;Allan&lt;/a&gt; if he was chosen as the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Tower\"&gt;Battle Tower&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"alchemist\"&gt;alchemist&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Potion of Wisdom is found at &lt;a href=\"Geshniz%27s%20Headquarters\"&gt;Geshniz's Headquarters&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt;, in the possession of &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; General &lt;a href=\"Geshniz\"&gt;Geshniz&lt;/a&gt; (she must be killed to obtain it). Her headquarters are located through a teleporter next to &lt;a href=\"Maxos%20Temple\"&gt;Maxos Temple&lt;/a&gt;, to reach it you'll need to use &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Form\"&gt;dragon form&lt;/a&gt; and destroy all the nests and ballista towers in the south and west/northwest.\nYou can use the Potion of Wisdom to permanently gain 5 points of Intelligence. However, this will use up the potion and prevents you from completing the quest, so it's only a good idea if you chose &lt;a href=\"Barbatos\"&gt;Barbatos&lt;/a&gt; as your alchemist. Once you have the potion, return to the Battle Tower and give it to Allan."}
