{"id": "10595", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10595", "title": "Witch (Original Sin 2)", "text": "The Witch is a &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;mage class&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nSummary.\nWitch is a mage who deals in &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; skills. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt;. Their primary weapon is a dagger. \nThe witches starting spells and skills are &lt;a href=\"Mosquito%20Swarm\"&gt;Mosquito Swarm&lt;/a&gt;, an offensive necromancer spell that summons mosquitos at their enemies. This spell is particularly useful in combination with the Witches talent &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Leech&lt;/a&gt;, due to bleeding effect the spell causes and potential healing they may get if they stand upon the spilled blood. Their second starting spell is &lt;a href=\"Raise%20Bloated%20Corpse\"&gt;Raise Bloated Corpse&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to raise any fallen body to do their bidding. Their final third skill is &lt;a href=\"Chloroform\"&gt;Chloroform&lt;/a&gt; which allows the Witch to destroy magical armour and put their enemies to sleep at distance.\nOutside combat the Witches can use their civil skill &lt;a href=\"Persuasion\"&gt;Persuasion&lt;/a&gt; to achieve their goals. \nMercenary Taylia.\nTaylia is an &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Elves\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be &lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Recruiting%20Mercenaries\"&gt;hired&lt;/a&gt; from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. Her role on the battlefield is that of witch, a mage who relies on &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; magic and scoundrel skills to defeat her enemies.\nDetailed description.\nList of all skills available.\nWitch is a class focused on casting &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; skills and &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; spells. Following table shows all spells which Witch can learn as they level up and invest points in respective combat abilities."}
{"id": "6146", "revid": "54598427", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6146", "title": "Witchcraft", "text": "Filled with the best buffs and debuffs in the game, Witchcraft skills are great for a supportive role. With low AP costs on many of the best spells, like 3 AP for Oath, which gives a 50% damage increase for 3 turns, this skill set has a lot to offer. Its best damage dealer, Destroy Summon, almost never comes into play, but against the Winter King, or if one of your own summons gets charmed, it can end any summons existence on our plane with no problem.\nThe two undead summons offered are extremely tanky versus earth and poison based enemies, though later in the game the 10% knockdown chance is blocked by one rank of Body Building, and the DPS on them is not the highest.\nBest Skills: Oath of Desecration for your DPS, Absorb the Elements to buff your tank, and Drain Willpower/Soulsap to shut down a boss.\nWitchcraft is the only ability that does not unlock any talents.\nOriginal Sin.\nEnhanced Edition.\nThe bracket after the CD of each skill indicates the minimum cooldown (achieved when INT is 15 or higher).\n\u221e) Can only be cast once per combat."}
