{"id": "12338", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12338", "title": "Worm Tremor", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;novice Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive geomancer skill that allows caster to conjure poisonous worms that will immobilise all characters in a target area up to 13 meters from the caster. The skill itself will deal earth damage to all characters in 4 meter impact radius of the skill. All characters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Entangled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Entangled&lt;/a&gt; status effect which will immobilise them and inflict additional poison damage for 2 turns. Note that the poison damage will heal all &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; affected by the status effect. Besides immobilising this status effect will lower &lt;a href=\"Dodging%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Dodging&lt;/a&gt; by 70 %.\nNote that some movement utilising skills are not affected by the &lt;a href=\"Entangled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Entangled&lt;/a&gt; status effect and as such this status will not prevent characters from using these skills. The skills not affected by the Entangled status effect are: &lt;a href=\"Blitz%20Attack\"&gt;Blitz Attack&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Backlash\"&gt;Backlash&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Nether%20Swap\"&gt;Nether Swap&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shade%20Shift\"&gt;Shade Shift&lt;/a&gt;.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is not reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. Since is a novice Geomancer skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 4. \n skill is one of the few magic-based skills that does not have a scroll.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Geomancer ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Geomancer).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist earth damage if they have: Earth Immunity Status and high enough Earth Resistance (which lowers earth damage done).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Geomancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only &lt;a href=\"Gareth%20Pryce\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; throughout the game on &lt;a href=\"the%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;the Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;, provided their demands are met."}
