{"id": "21437", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21437", "title": "Zandalor Trunks", "text": ""}
{"id": "2463", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2463", "title": "Zandalor the Wise", "text": "Zandalor the Wise is a wizard of great importance throughout most of the \"Divinity\" &lt;a href=\"series\"&gt;series&lt;/a&gt;. He first appeared in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\" seeking &lt;a href=\"Marked%20Ones\"&gt;Marked Ones&lt;/a&gt; before allying with &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; against the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt;. His next appearance was in \"&lt;a href=\"Child%20of%20the%20Chaos\"&gt;Child of the Chaos&lt;/a&gt;\", raising concerns about Lucian's decision to raise Damian. He is a prominent character in ', appearing in both \"&lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis\"&gt;Ego Draconis&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Flames%20of%20Vengeance\"&gt;Flames of Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;\". His most recent mainline appearance was in ', although he has also made a brief appearance in \"\".\nBackground.\nOne of the many wizards who took part in the wizard wars alongside &lt;a href=\"Maxos\"&gt;Maxos&lt;/a&gt; and Bellegar, Zandalor is one of the longest living humans on &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. Little is known of his life between the war and 4 AR when he had become the last of his kind and the keeper of the &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;; keeper of its memory. After he had spent his lifetime to preserve &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;, he took up residence in &lt;a href=\"Silverglen\"&gt;Silverglen&lt;/a&gt;, but now he fears that his private affairs have done more to harm it.\nZandalor was the Sorcerer who trained the White Witch &lt;a href=\"Icara\"&gt;Icara&lt;/a&gt; and her sister, the Conduit &lt;a href=\"Leandra\"&gt;Leandra&lt;/a&gt;. He was in a relationship with both of them, but finally chose Icara. This is the reason why Leandra cut the soul forge between Icara and fled, and got corrupted by the Void.\nHe tried to keep &lt;a href=\"Leandra\"&gt;Leandra&lt;/a&gt; from entering the First Garden to open &lt;a href=\"the%20Godbox\"&gt;the Godbox&lt;/a&gt; and free the &lt;a href=\"Void%20Dragon\"&gt;Void Dragon&lt;/a&gt;. But Leandra and her &lt;a href=\"Death%20Knight\"&gt;Death Knight&lt;/a&gt;s ambushed him and he was near death.\nHis next known appearance is in 1218 AD where he encounters &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; who is near death after being attacked by the &lt;a href=\"dragon%20rider\"&gt;dragon rider&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"John\"&gt;John&lt;/a&gt;, near &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;. His objective is to gather the Marked Ones, as they are the only people who can oppose the Black Ring's plans. After two of the Marked Ones are killed by the Black Ring, he takes the Lucian - the last Marked One - to the old chambers of the &lt;a href=\"Council%20of%20Seven\"&gt;Council of Seven&lt;/a&gt;, where he seeks to reform the Council so he can make the hero into the Divine One.\nAfter reforming the Council, Zandalor successfully carries out the ritual to start the Hero's transition into the Divine One, but before he and the Council can bring them back to life, Duke &lt;a href=\"Janus%20Ferol\"&gt;Janus Ferol&lt;/a&gt; arrives. Revealing his true demonic form, he kills the entire Council except for Zandalor (who he wanted to save for last) and &lt;a href=\"Kroxy\"&gt;Kroxy&lt;/a&gt; (who was playing dead). He escaped the Council chambers with the help of &lt;a href=\"Arhu\"&gt;Arhu&lt;/a&gt;, who was hiding nearby.\nIn the two months following their escape, Zandalor and Arhu encounter Lucian again whilst fighting some Black Ring imps. Zandalor urges the now Divine One to stop the Demon as soon as possible, directing them to the dragon known as &lt;a href=\"Patriarch\"&gt;Patriarch&lt;/a&gt;. Zandalor with Arhu are at the exit of the Demon's lair awaiting Lucian's return to find he is carrying the baby &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Damian&lt;/a&gt; in their arms. Zandalor questions Lucian's decision to save and raise the babe, expressing concern over the babe's latent demon power.\nAfter the Divine One's rise to power, Zandalor became &lt;a href=\"Lucian%20the%20Divine\"&gt;Lucian's&lt;/a&gt; main advisor. It was he who first felt the dark teachings of &lt;a href=\"Ygerna\"&gt;Ygerna&lt;/a&gt; and warned Lucian, leading to her capture and execution. When the war started Zandalor pleaded with Lucian that &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Damian&lt;/a&gt; had gone too far and had to be put down. Lucian however, like before, couldn't bring himself to kill Damian and left Damian behind in Nemesis, much to Zandalor's dismay.\nWhen Damian returned in 1244 AD and started a new war, Zandalor fought alongside the armies of &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. However, when news of Lucian's death reached his ears Zandalor was greatly saddened. Nevertheless, many years later when a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; was cornered by &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20slayer\"&gt;Slayers&lt;/a&gt;, Zandalor teleported in and defended the knight allowing it to escape. This made the slayers accuse Zandalor of treason and being a dragon sympathizer causing his fall from grace and flight into hiding.\nZandalor first appears before &lt;a href=\"The%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Slayer&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt; they met the last dragon knight, &lt;a href=\"Talana\"&gt;Talana&lt;/a&gt;. He speaks of the powers and responsibility given to the Slayer by Talana. He appears for the second time within the entrance hall of the &lt;a href=\"Maxos%20Temple\"&gt;Maxos Temple&lt;/a&gt;, reminding the Knight of the role Ygerna will play, whilst indirectly comparing the Knight to the late Divine. Later, he appears a at &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island\"&gt;Sentinel Island&lt;/a&gt; to explain a few things about the tower. He is met once again in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;, where he needs the Slayer's help closing the rifts and aids them to obtain the shield needed to journey into the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Hall of Echoes&lt;/a&gt;. Like the Dragon Knight, Zandalor was also deceived by &lt;a href=\"Ygerna\"&gt;Ygerna&lt;/a&gt; and helped bring her back to life, assuming it would kill Damian due to their improper &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Forge\"&gt;soul forging&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhilst the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; is in the Hall of Echoes, the Black Ring besieged Aleroth, Zandalor in an attempt to hold the siege line disables one of the barriers around &lt;a href=\"Behrlihn\"&gt;Behrlihn&lt;/a&gt;'s prison and repurposes it to stop the city's destruction. He tells general &lt;a href=\"Augustus\"&gt;Augustus&lt;/a&gt; to search for Behrlihn, who in turn sends Rhode to try and find him, but &lt;a href=\"Bellegar\"&gt;Bellegar&lt;/a&gt; opposes his goal; he points out that Zandalor was also certain of his plan to bring Ygerna back to life, and that bringing back &lt;a href=\"Behrlihn\"&gt;Behrlihn&lt;/a&gt; could cause more harm than good once more.\nAt the end of the \"Dragon Knight Saga\", Zandalor stands by Lucian as the Divine One returns from &lt;a href=\"Plane%20of%20Hypnerotomachia\"&gt;Plane of Hypnerotomachia&lt;/a&gt;."}
