{"id": "2339", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2339", "title": "ZixZax", "text": "ZixZax the Almost-Wise, sometimes referred to as Zixzax, is an &lt;a href=\"Imps\"&gt;imp&lt;/a&gt; historian who has travelled &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; for eons in his quest for preserving knowledge.\nBackground.\nZixZax is an imp historian of unknown origin who was ordered by the Gods to record the history of everything. During his travels he came across many prominent figures about which he wrote books and taught magic to aspiring mages such as &lt;a href=\"Icara\"&gt;Icara&lt;/a&gt;. During his quest for knowledge he discovered that the time itself will come to an end. This discovery pushed him to search for a way to prevent such an event to occur. One day he came upon a &lt;a href=\"Star%20Stone\"&gt;Star Stone&lt;/a&gt; at the border of &lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt; a distorted plane where the Ranaar reside. This stone led him to the &lt;a href=\"End%20of%20Time\"&gt;End of Time&lt;/a&gt; where he was stuck until the &lt;a href=\"Scarlett%20and%20Roderick\"&gt;Source Hunters&lt;/a&gt; arrived there in 4 AR and he gave them the red &lt;a href=\"Teleporter%20Pyramid\"&gt;Teleporter Pyramid&lt;/a&gt; in his gratitude as he could now freely travel once more. However this freedom was cut short for he had to request the Source Hunters help once more as the &lt;a href=\"Homestead\"&gt;Homestead&lt;/a&gt; was under an attack. Outside of this ZixZax helped the Source Hunters in their quest to make &lt;a href=\"30-Year%20Old%20Whisky\"&gt;30-Year Old Whisky&lt;/a&gt;. \nSeveral centuries later he reappear at &lt;a href=\"Stormfist%20Castle\"&gt;Stormfist Castle&lt;/a&gt; in 1218 AD where he approaches the Marked One &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; and comments that he is perfectly in middle of Order and Chaos. After remarking that he would write a book about him he asks the Divine to let him look at the teleporter pyramids he is carrying. ZixZax exclaims that he will use them to search for more Teleporter Pyramids as he steals them from the Divine. This theft left the Marked One effectively imprisoned at the castle as he was against his will, forced into a role of Lord Protector, a bodyguard of &lt;a href=\"Janus%20Ferol\"&gt;Janus Ferol&lt;/a&gt;. \nDuring his travels ZixZax is imprisoned at the &lt;a href=\"Council%20of%20the%20Seven%20%28Location%29\"&gt;Council of the Seven&lt;/a&gt; by a Succubus who waited there for Zandalor and Lucian. &lt;a href=\"The%20Succubus\"&gt;The Succubus&lt;/a&gt; is subsequently slain by Lucian after he and Zandalor arrive at the Council. With the Succubus slain ZixZax was freed and immediately confronted by the Divine about the theft. ZixZax willingly returns the Teleporter Pyramids and explains the Divine what he knows about the origins of the &lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Lord of Chaos&lt;/a&gt;. \nLittle is known of his whereabouts directly after Lucians ascension, however in 1238 AD, there were sightings of an Imp Historian upon Nemesis a plane now ruled by &lt;a href=\"demons\"&gt;demons&lt;/a&gt; from Hell who had overthrown the Ranaar. There he had helped a trapped &lt;a href=\"Hero%20%28Beyond%20Divinity%29\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; and their &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Death Knight&lt;/a&gt; companion to escape from a hole by giving them Teleporter Pyramid. \nDecades later in 1300 AD ZixZax encounters &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the last Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Maxos%20Temple\"&gt;Maxos Temple&lt;/a&gt; where he introduces himself to them and explains that he used the teleporter pyramids he stole from Lucian to travel between dimensions and due to Lucian keeping the pyramids after his conflict with the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; he is now trapped in Rivellon. He remarks subsequently that this is the cause of his moniker 'Almost-Wise' as he cannot travel between dimensions with just the power of words. As an immortal historian he has acquired vast amount of knowledge which the Dragon Knight used to decipher parchments in archaic Common Rivellonian and lend &lt;a href=\"George%20Gremory\"&gt;George Gremory&lt;/a&gt; an ancient draconian dictionary. "}
{"id": "13521", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13521", "title": "Zombie", "text": "Zombies are the shambling undead.\nBiology.\nThe resurrected, decaying corpses of the dead, zombies are usually found in graveyards or in the vicinity of necromancers.\nAs with their &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;skeletal&lt;/a&gt; counterparts, they are weak against fire and lightning, but resistant to spiritual and poison damage.\nVariants.\nCorpse.\nThe basic form of zombie, they shamble towards their target and swing at them with their arms.\nDark corpse.\nIn addition to a poisonous attack, the dark variant can throw poison projectiles.\nGhoul.\nA larger form of zombie, their flesh is more blistered than that of others. Has poisonous melee attack.\nGreater Ghoul.\nMore powerful version of Ghoul, the greater variant has a poisonous melee attack.\nZombie.\nTougher than the basic corpse, there is very little difference other than their basic stats.\nDark Zombie.\nShoots poisonous projectiles."}
{"id": "8624", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8624", "title": "Zombie Jake", "text": "Zombie Jake is a natural &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; who has appeared several times across &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; in 4 AR, 1218 AD and 1300 AD.\nBackground.\n\"Divine Divinity\".\nZombie Jake can be defeated up to three times. He is difficult to kill early in the game despite being encountered twice in the starting location, so saving the game before battling him is recommended. The first two times he is killed rewards 10,000 exp each. A third kill rewards 17,500 plus a reputation point.\nThe three Zombie Jake encounters are:\n\"Divinity II: Flames of Vengeance\".\nZombie Jake is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Eerie%20Undercroft\"&gt;Eerie Undercroft&lt;/a&gt; under a brothel belonging to &lt;a href=\"Madam%20Eve\"&gt;Madam Eve&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Lanilor%20Lane\"&gt;Lanilor Lane&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;. He has murdered four victims at &lt;a href=\"Madame%20Eve%27s\"&gt;Madame Eve's&lt;/a&gt;, but the Champions refuse to send any men to investigate the matter, due to the bigger threats to Aleroth's safety elsewhere. You are asked to help, beginning the quest &lt;a href=\"Murders%20in%20the%20Rue%20Lanilor\"&gt;Murders in the Rue Lanilor&lt;/a&gt;. After finding several clues, you eventually discover the entrance to the Eerie Undercroft. Acquiring a pair of crystals within allows you to open the door to Zombie Jake.\nInteractions with Player Character.\n&lt;a href=\"Mindread\"&gt;Mindread&lt;/a&gt;ing \nIt is possible to bypass this mindread by reading &lt;a href=\"Books%20and%20notes%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; titled \"&lt;a href=\"Corpse-stained%20Manuscript\"&gt;Corpse-stained Manuscript&lt;/a&gt;\" found in a chest near the southwest corner of the room, reveals that he's using the victims' corpses for a spell that makes him invincible. You need to awaken the victims as zombies by disturbing their graves, and slaughter all four, to stop the spell and kill him. A chest appears in the centre of the room containing &lt;a href=\"Zombie%20Jake%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Zombie Jake's Ring&lt;/a&gt;, needed for Clue II of the main plot quest, &lt;a href=\"To%20Find%20a%20Wizard\"&gt;To Find a Wizard&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Divinity: Original Sin\".\nCouncillor Jake's murder is the reason the Source Hunters appeared in &lt;a href=\"Cyseal\"&gt;Cyseal&lt;/a&gt; in the first place. After an &lt;a href=\"A%20Mysterious%20Murder\"&gt;investigation&lt;/a&gt;, they find that the apprentice healer &lt;a href=\"Evelyn\"&gt;Evelyn&lt;/a&gt; stole his body and brought it back from the dead. He is encountered as Zombie Jake after defeating Evelyn, and sells legendary &lt;a href=\"Orignal%20Sin%20items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt;. He also tells the Source Hunters that he was one of the Immaculates, and was murdered by &lt;a href=\"Leandra\"&gt;Leandra&lt;/a&gt;'s sister, &lt;a href=\"Icara\"&gt;Icara&lt;/a&gt;. Evelyn stole his body because she wanted to know how he became so close to Leandra.\nDue to Larian not treating Divinity's plot and chronology as being set in stone, it's unclear if this is the same Jake found in Aleroth (as Cyseal isn't even in &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt;) or just a reference to him. Considering &lt;a href=\"Thelyron%20Hashnitor\"&gt;Thelyron&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Esmeralda\"&gt;Esmeralda&lt;/a&gt;'s presence, however, he is definitely meant to act as the 'Zombie Jake' of this game."}
{"id": "9068", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9068", "title": "Zombie Jake's Ring", "text": "Zombie Jake's Ring is a in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nDefeating &lt;a href=\"Zombie%20Jake\"&gt;Zombie Jake&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Eerie%20Undercroft\"&gt;Eerie Undercroft&lt;/a&gt; under &lt;a href=\"Madame%20Eve%27s\"&gt;Madame Eve's&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Lanilor%20Lane\"&gt;Lanilor Lane&lt;/a&gt; causes a small chest to appear on the altar in the center of the room containing the ring. It is needed for Clue II of &lt;a href=\"To%20Find%20a%20Wizard\"&gt;To Find a Wizard&lt;/a&gt;.\nExamining the ring reveals: \"This ring, dented and faded with the aeons, carries an engraved message: \"Gold is what the Violet Blast craves most\"\" - a clue concerning the &lt;a href=\"Champion%20Academy%20Orbs\"&gt;orbs&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Champion%20Academy\"&gt;Champion Academy&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Behrlihn\"&gt;Behrlihn&lt;/a&gt; explains that ring was stolen from Thelyron Hashnitor, a Commander of the Council during the Wizard Wars."}
{"id": "14116", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14116", "title": "Zorl-Stissa", "text": "Zorl-Stissa is one of the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Seven%20Gods\"&gt;Seven Gods&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and creator of &lt;a href=\"lizard\"&gt;lizard&lt;/a&gt; race.\nBackground.\nZorl-Stissa was one of the seven Eternal lords who used to serve the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"God%20King\"&gt;God King&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0until\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Fane\"&gt;Fane&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0told them about his discovery and they began to rebel and banished the God King and his people into the Void.\u00a0\nAfter she had banished the God King she and other six lords created mortal races in their resemblance so that they could gain more power through worship (and their deceased souls in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Hall of Echoes&lt;/a&gt;). Zorl-Stissa created the lizards who are the most proud race of all the seven races of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;.\nAppearance.\nWhen seen in a vision or met in Hall of Echoes she appears like a spirit surrounded by golden light. She wears a three-layered crown. Her eyes are the colour of onyx and\u00a0she has feathered shoulders. Her scales are color of red.\nGodwoken Champions.\nAs\u00a0one of the Seven Gods, Zorl-Stissa had her own champions who could attempt to become a Divine."}
