{"id": "2530", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2530", "title": "A Shaman's Ransom", "text": "A Shaman's Ransom is a &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; given by &lt;a href=\"Aurelius\"&gt;Aurelius&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Champion%20Harbour\"&gt;Champion Harbour&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". \nDetailed Walkthrough.\nAurelius asks you to bring him the head of a notorious &lt;a href=\"goblin\"&gt;goblin&lt;/a&gt; chief named &lt;a href=\"Svadilfari\"&gt;Svadilfari&lt;/a&gt;. Completing this quest will not cause the Champions to turn hostile and &lt;a href=\"Talana\"&gt;Talana&lt;/a&gt; will remark how one has \"a novel way of giving head\".\nUpon speaking to Svadilfari, &lt;a href=\"The%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;The Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; is given the option take up the goblins offer of killing Aurelius; this offer must be accepted at this stage to be able to continue, otherwise ones only choice is to defeat the imp, regardless of if the quest &lt;a href=\"Death%20of%20a%20Champion\"&gt;Death of a Champion&lt;/a&gt; has been taken.\nTravel to the &lt;a href=\"Champion%20Harbour\"&gt;Champion Harbour&lt;/a&gt;'s interior and kill Aurelius as requested and return Svadilfari, who in turn will attempt to kill the Dragon Knight. Once his health has been severely diminished, Svadilfari will abandon the cave and take flight outside. The knight must change to dragon form and finish the goblin off before the quest can be completed."}
{"id": "5999", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5999", "title": "A Shell on the Beach", "text": "A Shell on the Beach is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%20Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"\nWalkthrough.\nFrom the &lt;a href=\"Waypoint%20Shrine\"&gt;Waypoint Shrine&lt;/a&gt; on the south beach, head southeast along the coastal path. At the end of the path &lt;a href=\"Ishmashell\"&gt;Ishmashell&lt;/a&gt; can be found lamenting being beached and want to return to the sea. Speak to the shell and he will explain his plight and desire to return to the watery depths, offering a reward in exchange for assistance. \nIf the &lt;a href=\"Source%20Hunters\"&gt;Source Hunters&lt;/a&gt; disagree, they will resort to a rock, paper scissors challenge to determine the path taken. The choices made will affect their ego or altruism. \nIf the decision to return him to the sea is made, Ishmashell will return to the depths and throw out a chest containing &lt;a href=\"Mermaid%27s%20kiss\"&gt;Mermaid's kiss&lt;/a&gt; and potentially other items. If taken by the Source Hunters, he can be sold or consumed for a +10% permanent Water Resistance bonus. You can also cook him to make Cooked Ishmashell and eat him for infectious disease."}
