{"id": "2063", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2063", "title": "Abanayabar", "text": "Abanayabar is a talking tree, originally from &lt;a href=\"Teneb%20Tiriel\"&gt;Teneb Tiriel&lt;/a&gt; in 1218 AD, with a cutting taking root under the &lt;a href=\"watermill\"&gt;watermill&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley%20village\"&gt;Broken Valley village&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nThe famous talking tree of the Dark Forest, found to the east of &lt;a href=\"Fiu%20Nimble\"&gt;Fiu Nimble&lt;/a&gt; in 1218 AD he has been convinced by a &lt;a href=\"dwarf\"&gt;dwarf&lt;/a&gt; that all wood cutters imbue magic powers that can cut him down, resulting in fear of mortals and aggression towards any who attempt to approach him; slinging fireballs and raising the undead to protect himself.\nPrior to 1230 a branch cutting was taken by &lt;a href=\"Buadrim%20Venomclaw\"&gt;Buadrim Venomclaw&lt;/a&gt; and planted in the basement of Broken Valley Village's watermill. By 1300 AD, this cutting is working on alchemy with Buadrim, who is going by the name of Upton; however, he cannot say if the original tree still stands following the great war."}
{"id": "14235", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14235", "title": "Abandoned Camp", "text": "Abandoned camp is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Locations\"&gt;camp&lt;/a&gt; on the outskirts of abandoned harbour in the north of &lt;a href=\"Reapers%27%20Eye\"&gt;Reapers' Eye&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nPrior to the camps abandonment, this was the main outpost of &lt;a href=\"the%20Seekers\"&gt;the Seekers&lt;/a&gt; on the island. Upon its discovery by the &lt;a href=\"Magisters\"&gt;Magisters&lt;/a&gt;, the Seekers were assaulted. Those who failed to escape and were not killed, were converted into &lt;a href=\"Shriekers\"&gt;Shriekers&lt;/a&gt;; their bodies trussed upon crucifixes to act as defences to prevent the Seekers from retaking the site. \nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"Escape%20from%20Reaper%27s%20Eye\"&gt;Escape from Reaper's Eye&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "9194", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9194", "title": "Abandoned Catacomb", "text": "The Abandoned Catacomb is a &lt;a href=\"Locations%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;location&lt;/a&gt; under the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Market\"&gt;Great Market&lt;/a&gt; district of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; that is accessible during the events of \"\".\nLayout.\nThe trapdoor entrance is the southeast of the district, on the grass directly east of &lt;a href=\"Caracalla\"&gt;Caracalla's&lt;/a&gt; pyre. You'll find a few &lt;a href=\"chest\"&gt;chest&lt;/a&gt;s in the catacomb, but no &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Quests\"&gt;quests&lt;/a&gt; take place here and there are no unique or &lt;a href=\"Armor%20set\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt; items within. Exploration of the catacomb is purely optional, and due to the relatively low level of enemies, is most beneficial in terms of &lt;a href=\"exp\"&gt;exp&lt;/a&gt;erience if done early in the game. (Note: In \"\" the entrance the Abandoned Catacomb is selectable but locked, without a key to be found. Even if unlocked using the game's console commands, attempting to enter does nothing.)\nDescription.\nThe catacomb is occupied by level 36 &lt;a href=\"ghost\"&gt;ghost&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s, and &lt;a href=\"zombie\"&gt;zombie&lt;/a&gt;s. In addition to the chests there are many crates and urns which may contain random loot or up to around 300 gold each.\nHead south from the entrance and &lt;a href=\"Lockpick%20%28Divinity%20II%29\"&gt;lockpick&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"chest\"&gt;chest&lt;/a&gt; along the eastern wall for random loot. Continue south, fighting the &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; along the way. When you reach the east-west-north intersection, proceed east. Towards the end up the tunnel, climb the small wooden staircase and open the unlocked chest on the northern platform.\nReturn to the intersection and continue west. Go up the incline as it curves north. At the far end of this tunnel is an unlocked golden chest containing more random loot.\nEnemies.\nAll enemies are level 36:\nMaps.\nClick images to enlarge.\nLocation of the Abandoned Catacomb (entrance at \"6\" on map):\nMap of the Abandoned Catacomb:"}
{"id": "9006", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9006", "title": "Abandoned Cave", "text": "The Abandoned Cave is a &lt;a href=\"Locations%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;location&lt;/a&gt; under the &lt;a href=\"Mardaneus%20Plaza\"&gt;Mardaneus Plaza&lt;/a&gt; district of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; that is accessible during the events of \"\".\nDescription.\nThe trapdoor entrance is behind a fence, northwest of the &lt;a href=\"Circle%20of%20Trust%20Inn\"&gt;Circle of Trust Inn&lt;/a&gt; (a.k.a. Emergency Barracks). You'll find several &lt;a href=\"Ores\"&gt;ore veins&lt;/a&gt; and a few &lt;a href=\"chest\"&gt;chest&lt;/a&gt;s in the cave, but no quests take place here and there are no unique or &lt;a href=\"Armor%20set\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt; items within. Exploration of the cave is purely optional, and due to the relatively low level of enemies, is most beneficial in terms of &lt;a href=\"exp\"&gt;exp&lt;/a&gt;erience if done early in the game.\nThis cave is occupied by level 36 &lt;a href=\"Ghost\"&gt;Ghost&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s, and &lt;a href=\"Zombie\"&gt;Zombie&lt;/a&gt;s. In addition to the chests and ores, there are a significant number of crates and barrels which may contain random loot or up to around 300 gold.\nProceed east from the entrance, then turn left (north) to find an unlocked chest containing random loot. Turn around and head south, following the curve east. In the large room with a campfire, notice the wooden platform structure above the ground. Climb the rocks to your right (south), to find the Abandoned Key. Cross the platform to the north side, and unlock the Abandoned Chest containing random loot. Drop down to the ground, and continue east.\nThere are three &lt;a href=\"Red%20Ore\"&gt;Red Ore&lt;/a&gt; veins near the corner as the tunnel curves south. In the next room there is a fork where you can continue south up and go up a curving ramp, or turn east. There are enemies to slaughter to the south, but nothing else, so kill them first if you wish, then take the east fork.\nYou'll find three &lt;a href=\"Black%20Rock\"&gt;Black Rock&lt;/a&gt; ore veins along the tunnel heading east. You'll soon reach another room with a fork, where you can continue east or go south. Head south, mining the three &lt;a href=\"Droxlerite\"&gt;Droxlerite&lt;/a&gt; veins along the way. Further south is a finished area, containing some furnishings and storage space. In the small room to the left (east) you'll find a locked chest along the north wall, which can be &lt;a href=\"Lockpick%20%28Divinity%20II%29\"&gt;lockpick&lt;/a&gt;ed for random loot.\nReturn to the fork and proceed east. The tunnel curves south, where you'll find two &lt;a href=\"Iron\"&gt;Iron&lt;/a&gt; ore veins near a large, glowing blue mushroom. Continue south, following the tunnel as it curves up and east. At the end you'll find an unlocked chest containing random loot.\nEnemies.\nAll enemies are level 36:"}
