{"id": "16787", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16787", "title": "Ability Points", "text": "Ability Points (AP) are points that are used to determine the available number of moves a character can take during a turn. This statistic was first introduced in \"\" and returned in \"Divinity: Original Sin 2]]\". In \"Original Sin\" the initial, total and recharge per turn is statistically derived, in \"Original Sin 2\" these figures are generally fixed.\nUsed for skills, movement and environmental interaction during combat, ability point requirements are partially derived from other factors, such as character &amp; weapon level, points invested in &lt;a href=\"Speed\"&gt;Speed&lt;/a&gt; or weapon/armour modifiers to Movement.\n\"Original Sin 2\" introduced a secondary form of AP, Source Points (SP), which allow the use of &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; based abilities. Each character has a maximum of three points available; however, these do not recharge over time, but through the acquisition of &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "16569", "revid": "25368351", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16569", "title": "Ablewether", "text": "Vonda Ablewether is a &lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; captain residing at &lt;a href=\"Driftwood\"&gt;Driftwood&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"The%20Black%20Bull\"&gt;Black Bull tavern&lt;/a&gt; in 1242 AD.\nBackground.\nV. Ablewether is a captain, who was hired by &lt;a href=\"The%20Magisters\"&gt;Magisters&lt;/a&gt; to transport magical artifacts, materials and Deathfog from &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Reimond\"&gt;Reimond&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Driftwood\"&gt;Driftwood&lt;/a&gt;. However her ship sank when she was mislead by a false lighthouse created by &lt;a href=\"Lohar\"&gt;Lohar&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"dwarves\"&gt;dwarves&lt;/a&gt;. As her ship crashed into cliffs all of her crew died either by drowning or deathfog. \nAs a sole survivor and captain of the ship, she is haunted by a member of her crew in her room at the Black Bull tavern."}
