{"id": "20214", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20214", "title": "Acid (Status)", "text": "Acid is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Environmental%20status%20effects\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nAcid is a negative environmental status which destroys Physical armour of the afflicted character per every turn they are afflicted by it. Once physical armour is destroyed it will stop causing any damage, however it will prevent armour restoration that is smaller than the amount of physical damage it deals. Therefore its main usage is to render character vulnerable to status effects such as &lt;a href=\"Knocked-Down%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Knocked-Down&lt;/a&gt;. Acid status effect is most often accompanied by poison damage which destroys Magic Armour.\nCause.\nThere are many ways through which acid status effect can be triggered. On &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; it is the contact with \"cursed poison surface\" or \"cursed poison cloud\" which will cause acid. These surfaces are created casting &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;curse&lt;/a&gt; on \"poison surface\" or \"poison cloud\".\nIn combat acid may be caused in-directly by throwing &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Poison%20Flask\"&gt;Cursed Poison Flask&lt;/a&gt; which will create \"cursed poison surface\" beneath its target or through spells and scrolls.\nTreatment.\nThe effects of acid can be treated by either countering its effects or by removing the status altogether. \nStatus counter.\nSince acid status effect mainly destroys physical armour any effect, spell or item that restores it may counter its effect. There are several ways to restore Physical armour. First is by investing in &lt;a href=\"Perseverance\"&gt;Perseverance&lt;/a&gt; combat skill which will restore Physical armour whenever said character is Knocked-Down or Petrified.\nSecond way to restore Physical armour is through contact with blessed oil surface, which has a chance of applying &lt;a href=\"Fortified%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Fortified&lt;/a&gt; status that restores Physical armour. Blessed oil surface can be create by casting &lt;a href=\"Bless%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Bless&lt;/a&gt; upon oil surface.\nConsuming items is one of the easier ways to restore armour. Most efficient of consumable items is &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Armour%20Potion\"&gt;Physical Armour Potion&lt;/a&gt; which can also be upgraded. If one runs out of potions then they may consume &lt;a href=\"Amadouvier\"&gt;Amadouvier&lt;/a&gt; however it is much less efficient. Efficiency of both of these can be improved through &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt;.\nArmour restoration through spells and scrolls is arguably the best way of physical armour restoration as it scales with character level and points invested in Geomancer &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;combat ability&lt;/a&gt;. \nStatus removal.\nAcid status effect is most efficiently removed by casting appropriate spells or using scrolls with said spells. "}
{"id": "5710", "revid": "2056997", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5710", "title": "Acid Breath", "text": "Description.\nConjures a cobra and breathes a cone of acid at the location of the caster. Hits all targets in the AoE for X-Y poison damage.\n55% base chance to set\nPoisoned deals damage over time."}
{"id": "12447", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12447", "title": "Acid Infusion", "text": "Acid Infusion is a &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning source skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive mixed skill that allows caster to change their summoned Incarnate's element to cursed poison. By changing the element, the Incarnate gains multiple boons associated with it. Its basic close attack will deal poison damage. Due to the Incarnate being infused with cursed poison it gains Poison Resistance + 120 % but it suffer from decreased resistances: Air Resistance - 20 %. Besides Poison resistance being increased the Incarnate becomes immune to &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status effect. Alongside this the Incarnate learns the Geomancer skill &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Dart\"&gt;Poison Dart&lt;/a&gt; and Geomancer source skill &lt;a href=\"Acid%20Spores\"&gt;Acid Spores&lt;/a&gt; for which it also gains + 2 &lt;a href=\"Source%20Points%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Source Points&lt;/a&gt;. Lastly it will receive + 10 points to &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; ability itself. \nNote that unlike the &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Infusion\"&gt;Poison Infusion&lt;/a&gt; the effects of cannot be achieved by summoning the Incarnate unto cursed poison surface.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into both &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted by combining any &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks out of which atleast one must be a source skillbook. Since is a mixed source skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from NPCs in the game.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift Bag: Pet Power allows this skill to be used on any summoned creature. This gift bag also shortens the cooldown of this skill from 3 turns to 1 turn. Following table shows what skills will specific summoned entity gain from . Note that there are no changes to the skill and bonuses granted by the skill to the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;, likewise all summoned entities gain source skill &lt;a href=\"Acid%20Spores\"&gt;Acid Spores&lt;/a&gt; and + 2 Source points."}
{"id": "22844", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22844", "title": "Acid Sparks (Original Sin 2)", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;tierless Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; released as part of in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; skill that allows caster to shoot up to two acid projectiles at their chosen area in 13 meter range. Each projectile deals poison damage and will jump at the closest targets up to 2 times in 5 meter range from the last target. \nAffected characters will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Acid%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Acid&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 2 turns which will destroy their Physical armour.\nSkillbook and Scroll.\n is a tierless skill that has no scroll or skillbook from which it can be learnt or cast. \nThis skill is exclusive to the &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Hungry%20Flower\"&gt;Hungry Flower&lt;/a&gt; as it acquires this skill when it is under the effect of &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Infusion\"&gt;Poison Infusion&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Acid%20Infusion\"&gt;Acid Infusion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; skills.\nModifiers.\n scales with &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt;, Level and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "10427", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10427", "title": "Acid Spores", "text": "Acid Spores is an &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;expert Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sourcery%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;source&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nSkill.\n is a offensive geomancer source skill that allows caster to shoot three spores filled with corrosive acid at target locations in 13 meter radius. Each spore does poison damage to all characters in 2 meter impact radius and creates a cursed poison cloud which lasts for 2 turns and then turns into poison cloud. \nCharacters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 3 turns and suffer damage directly to their health, with the exception of &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;. All characters standing in the cursed poison cloud will be afflicted &lt;a href=\"Acid%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Acid&lt;/a&gt; status effect which destroys Physical Armour for 1 turn. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 750 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Earth%20Skillbook\"&gt;High Tier Blank Earth Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a expert Geomancer skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 13.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 260 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves varies. The cost to cast the as a source skill is 3 Action Points and 2 &lt;a href=\"Source%20Points%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Source Points&lt;/a&gt;. The cost to cast scroll is only 3 Action Points.\nBoth the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Geomancer ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Geomancer).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist poison damage if they have: Poison Immunity Status and high enough Poison Resistance (which lowers poison damage done). Additionally any character that is Undead or has the talent &lt;a href=\"Undead%20%28talent%29\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;, will automatically have + 200 % Poison Resistance which will cause them to heal from all poison damage done.\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Geomancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only &lt;a href=\"Gareth%20Pryce\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; throughout the game on &lt;a href=\"the%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;the Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;, provided their demands are met."}
{"id": "5652", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5652", "title": "Action Points (Original Sin)", "text": "\"\" is a manaless game. It uses the Action Point System to Move, Attack and Use &lt;a href=\"Skills%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Skills&lt;/a&gt;.\nMaximum AP has a base of 7.\nStarting AP has a base of 2.\nTurn AP has a base of 3.5.\nFormula.\nformula_1\nformula_2\nformula_3\nMaximum.\nThere is no maximum AP, although the bar displayed in combat is limited to 31. If you have more, they will not be displayed, but the game will take them into account correctly and use the \"invisible\" AP first."}
