{"id": "6140", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6140", "title": "Aerotheurge (Original Sin)", "text": "Aerotheurge skills deal Int-Based Air damage. Many of their skills have a utility focus, such as teleporting, , shields and . Very few enemies have high so it provides reliable damage, if not as high as a &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt;'s Fire damage. Probably the best element to combine with a as it offers 3 different teleports. Its level 5 ability grants immune to , and in emergencies, and make for easy saves. also is a great skill for cleaning up the battlefield in case the start becoming more beneficial to your enemies. A 1-level dip into &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; with this grants , which turns into , and enemies are 30% more likely to be stunned.\nEnhanced Edition.\nThe bracket after the CD of each skill indicates the minimum cooldown (achieved when INT is 15 or higher).\n\u221e) Can only be cast once per combat."}
