{"id": "12150", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12150", "title": "Air Essence", "text": "Air essence is a type of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Crafting%23Crafting%20components\"&gt;crafting component&lt;/a&gt; in ' and '.\nCharacteristics.\nAir essence is an ingredient used for crafting &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; scrolls and potions such as &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Jellyfish%20Skin\"&gt;Potion of Jellyfish Skin&lt;/a&gt; and arrows.\nLocations.\nCreatures.\nFollowing table shows all creatures which have a chance to drop the item upon death. Highlighted creatures in this table have 100 % chance to drop said item. Note that creatures may drop other items as well.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for. Note that for more powerful Aerotheurge scrolls a better quality Air essence is required. If the scroll utilises base Air essence it is possible to use higher quality essence as substitute. In short you cannot use \"Air Essence\" in recipe requiring \"Alien Air Essence\" or \"High Quality Air Essence\"."}
{"id": "10953", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10953", "title": "Air Resistance Potion (Original Sin 2)", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"Consumables%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;consumable item&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nAir resistance potion is a consumable potion that grants 15% Air resistance for 3 turns. If character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt;, the potion will grant 30% Air resistance instead of 15%. The potions weight is 0.25 and its value is 30 gold.\nMedium air resistance potion is a consumable potion that grants 50% Air resistance for 3 turns. If character has Five-Star Diner talent, the potion will grant 100% Air resistance instead of 50%. The potions weight is 0.25 and its value is 45 gold.\nLarge air resistance potion is a consumable potion that grants 75% Air resistance for 2 turns. If character has Five-Star Diner talent, the potion will grant 150% Air resistance instead of 75%. The potions weight is 0.25 and its value is 150 gold.\nHuge air resistance potion is a consumable potion that grants 90% Air resistance for 2 turns. If character has Five-Star Diner talent, the potion will grant 180% Air resistance instead of 90%. The potions weight is 0.25 and its value is 450 gold.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of potions and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for. "}
