{"id": "2033", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2033", "title": "Alchemist", "text": "An Alchemist (also referred to as a herbalist) is a person who uses &lt;a href=\"herbs\"&gt;herbs&lt;/a&gt; and vials to craft &lt;a href=\"potions\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nYou must talk to your alchemist while you have the &lt;a href=\"Enchantments%2C%20Potions%20and%20Formulas\"&gt;formula&lt;/a&gt; you want them to learn on you. The formula then disappears and your alchemist learns the recipe. (Example: I have Healing 10 formula and talk to my alchemist. He learns Healing 10. The formula disappears.) If your alchemist already knows how to make the potion, you will keep the formula in your inventory.\nThe number of &lt;a href=\"Herbs\"&gt;ingredients&lt;/a&gt; you need depends on what level your &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Tower\"&gt;Battle Tower&lt;/a&gt; alchemy platform is. A level 3 platform only needs 1x Fanny Blossom and 3x Ginseng for a healing 10 potion. But a level 1 platform needs 2x Fanny Blossom and 5x Ginseng to make one. The &lt;a href=\"Master%20Herbalist\"&gt;Master Herbalist&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skills%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; also reduces the quantity of ingredients needed to craft portions."}
{"id": "14191", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14191", "title": "Alchemy", "text": "Alchemy is a passive &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20skills%23Way%20of%20the%20survivor\"&gt;Survivor skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThis skill allows player to create potions and poisons as well as mix potions."}
