{"id": "13716", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13716", "title": "Allan Brew", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Items%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29%23Potions\"&gt;potion&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"\nBackground.\nThe Allan Brew is first mentioned by &lt;a href=\"Allan%20%28Sentinel%20Island%29\"&gt;Allan&lt;/a&gt; when he pleads the aspiring &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; to recruit him, he mentions it possesses the power to make one Stronger, Wiser, and Faster. &lt;a href=\"Mindread\"&gt;Mindread&lt;/a&gt;ing him reveals Allan is a liar and has yet honed the ability to brew such a &lt;a href=\"Potions\"&gt;potion&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpon choosing Allan, he tries to avoid the subject of the Allan Brew by sending the Dragon Knight out to gather rare herbs and multiple items. His brew in the end turned out to be a tremendous success however, to Allan's amazement and bewilderment.\nCharacteristics.\nAllan Brew grants the player 36 resistance to every armour rating when drank. It is the strongest Resistance Potion in the game. \nIts relatively easy (with careful gear selection and only four +Ranged Armour &lt;a href=\"Enchantments%2C%20Potions%20and%20Formulas\"&gt;enchantments&lt;/a&gt;, no +Melee/Magic required) to reach a neat 60% to all resistances, and an Allan Brew is just strong enough to push 60% to the perfect cap of 66% while barehanded... the other resistance potions aren't good enough and require sacrificing Lifeline enchantments and such. The result is having the best possible damage resistance no matter the &lt;a href=\"Skills%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;skills&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; chosen, and it doesn't even require allocating any stat points at all if &lt;a href=\"charms\"&gt;charms&lt;/a&gt; are chosen carefully as well (all need to be at least +4, but that's doable in )."}
{"id": "2509", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2509", "title": "Allan Brew Confidential", "text": "Allan Brew Confidential is a &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". The quest is initiated by speaking to &lt;a href=\"Allan%20%28Sentinel%20Island%29\"&gt;Allan&lt;/a&gt; who is located at the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Tower\"&gt;Battle Tower&lt;/a&gt;'s alchemist platform.\nDetailed walkthrough.\nAllan will ask for whisperwood, black rose, earth root, and holy basil. Once these ingredients have been given to him, he will then ask for one more item: a dragon nail. \nOne the dragon nail has been given to him, he will begin to work on the potion. Talk to him again (which can be done immediately) and ask him for the potion. He will admit surprise that it worked, and that the alchemist platform needs more room to house these ingredients. "}
{"id": "13999", "revid": "4079189", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13999", "title": "Almira", "text": "Almira is a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; member and alleged &lt;a href=\"succubus\"&gt;succubus&lt;/a&gt; located at &lt;a href=\"Paradise%20Downs\"&gt;Paradise Downs&lt;/a&gt; in 1242 AD.\nBackground.\nAlmira is an ex-Black Ring and deserter who fled the cult because of her love for Magister &lt;a href=\"Mihaly\"&gt;Mihaly&lt;/a&gt;, who reciprocated her feelings and helped her flee from the &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Order\"&gt;Divine Order&lt;/a&gt; prison.\nDriftwood arc.\nShe will ask the player to clear the miasma which causes permanent \"decay\" effect in the area. To complete the quest player must kill the Harbinger of Doom.\nAfter completing the previous task she will ask the player to bring her the Swornbreaker schematic tablet from &lt;a href=\"the%20Blackpits\"&gt;the Blackpits&lt;/a&gt; excavation site; the same one &lt;a href=\"Ryker\"&gt;Ryker&lt;/a&gt; wants.\nNameless Isle arc.\nOn &lt;a href=\"Nameless%20Isle\"&gt;Nameless Isle&lt;/a&gt; she can give player the Swornbreaker schematic tablet if asked and also provide an alternative way of dealing with the Black Ring cultists who laid siege to the island: she allows the player to pose as her thrall to bypass the Ring without a fight."}
