{"id": "2425", "revid": "53418829", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2425", "title": "Amdusias", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"dragon\"&gt;dragon&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Maxos%20Temple\"&gt;Maxos Temple&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nHe was a fierce rival of &lt;a href=\"Lovis\"&gt;Lovis&lt;/a&gt; because only one of them could become a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt;. Lovis proved to be the best so he won the competition, resulting Amdusias becoming a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20priest\"&gt;Dragon priest&lt;/a&gt;. Following Lovis' failure to maintain order in &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt;, maxos cursed him and entrusted Amdusias with his soul.\nAmdusias loathed his master &lt;a href=\"Maxos\"&gt;Maxos&lt;/a&gt;, and will be infuriated when the aspiring &lt;a href=\"The%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; found out this silly yet wicked jibe directed towards the failed whelp of a Dragon Knight. The idea of the Dragon Knight succeeding the Maxos Temple trials and his ears being constantly besieged by the name of his master he despised to the very end is intolerable.\nHe has managed to discover the means to becoming a &lt;a href=\"Dragon\"&gt;Dragon&lt;/a&gt;, but is stuck in dragon form within Citadel, along with those who who betrayed Maxos until the Knight reverses the spell.\nAfter the Knight has defeated him in combat, he will then transcend to the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Hall of Echoes&lt;/a&gt;, where the Knight will encountered him again (in human form) at the arena."}
