{"id": "10984", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10984", "title": "Apple (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Apple is a &lt;a href=\"Consumables%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Food%20and%20Drink\"&gt;consumable item&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nApple is a simple fruit which may be used to make &lt;a href=\"Apple%20Juice\"&gt;Apple Juice&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Apple%20Pie%20Dough\"&gt;Apple pie dough&lt;/a&gt;. Apple itself heals 10% of maximum Vitality upon consuming and increases Poison resistance by 5%. If character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; the will heal 20% of maximum Vitality and increase Poison resistance by 10%. The effects last 3 turns.\nPoisoned apple is a fruit that was poisoned through various means (either &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Bottle%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;poison bottle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Zaikk%27s%20Talon\"&gt;Zaikk's Talon&lt;/a&gt;). Poisoning the will reduce its value to 0. Instead of healing it will deal poison damage equal to 10 % of the consumers maximum Vitality, rendering it unsafe for the living but safe for &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; and increase Poison resistance by 5 %. \nIf character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; the will deal poison damage equal to 20 % of the consumers maximum Vitality and increase the Poison resistance by 10 %. The effects last 3 turns. \nNote that poisoned item may be used in crafting, however the end product will be un-poisoned item.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of food and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for. "}
{"id": "17376", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17376", "title": "Apple Juice", "text": "Apple juice is a &lt;a href=\"Consumables%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Food%20and%20Drink\"&gt;consumable item&lt;/a&gt; in ' and '.\nCharacteristics.\nOriginal Sin II.\nApple juice is a drink which is made from an &lt;a href=\"Apple\"&gt;Apple&lt;/a&gt;. When consumed it will heal for + 10 % of maximum Vitality and grant + 10 % Poison resistance. Characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; are healed for 20 % maximum Vitality and gain + 20 % Poison resistance. Effects last 6 turns.\nPoisoned is a drink that was poisoned through various means (either &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Bottle%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;poison bottle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Zaikk%27s%20Talon\"&gt;Zaikk's Talon&lt;/a&gt;). Instead of healing it will deal poison damage equal to 10 % of the consumers maximum Vitality, rendering it unsafe for the living but safe for &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; and increase Poison resistance by 10 %. The effects last 6 turns.\nLocations.\nOriginal Sin 2.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of food and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs."}
