{"id": "12366", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12366", "title": "Arcane Stitch", "text": " is an &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;adept Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sourcery%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;source&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive hydrosophist skill that allows caster to fully restore all Magic Armour on themselves or on their chosen ally. If target character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Shell%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Magic Shell&lt;/a&gt; status effect the will restore the Magic Armour up to the increased maximum amount set by the status effect. Alongside restoring the entirety of Magic Armour this skill will also remove a large amount of negative status effects (listed below). Since this skill applies positive status effect it will always bypass armour. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophy\"&gt;Hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nList of all negative status effects removed:\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 800 gold. Since is a adept Hydrosophist source skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 9.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive skill that provides clear set bonuses. As such these bonuses by themselves cannot be increased, however they can stack with other items, skills or talents that provide them. \nThe only way to improve this skill is to increase its range and decrease its Action Point cost through skills or talents.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell hydrosophist spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met. Also note that &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Dreamer\"&gt;Lizard Dreamer&lt;/a&gt; requires a persuasion check to be passed in order to speak with him, otherwise he (and the whole encampment) will turn hostile. \nIt is also sold by &lt;a href=\"Hannag\"&gt;Hannag&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Cloisterwood\"&gt;Cloisterwood&lt;/a&gt;, however note that she needs to be saved from the &lt;a href=\"The%20Magisters\"&gt;Magister&lt;/a&gt;s first and she sells solely this hydrosophist spell alongside source spells from other combat abilities. "}
